1
00:00:20,254 --> 00:01:28,168
片名：国王与我

2
00:00:45,108 --> 00:01:45,168
本版本字幕由 Wendy's PaPa 翻译、整理、调校时间轴
This version subtitles by Wendy's PaPa

3
00:01:55,254 --> 00:02:00,668
泰国 1862年

4
00:02:09,254 --> 00:02:12,257
快点搬，快点搬，不能整天耗在这
Come on, lads, hurry!
We haven't got all day.

5
00:02:14,843 --> 00:02:17,221
船长，这就是泰国了吗
Is that it, captain? Are we here?

6
00:02:17,387 --> 00:02:19,973
对，这就是曼谷
Aye, laddie. That's Bangkok all right.

7
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:22,726
路易，路易
Louis! Oh, Louis!

8
00:02:22,893 --> 00:02:25,020
妈妈，曼谷到了
Mother! Look, there's Bangkok.

9
00:02:25,187 --> 00:02:27,940
我知道，这真令人兴奋
Yes, I know. Isn't it exciting?

10
00:02:28,482 --> 00:02:31,944
船长，告诉我为什么要抛下锚呢
有什么问题吗？
Captain, I heard them lowering
the anchor. ls anything wrong?

11
00:02:32,110 --> 00:02:35,364
我们在等待涨潮，只有那时才能入港
We have to wait for the afternoon
tide to carry us over the bar.

12
00:02:35,531 --> 00:02:37,199
原来是这样
Oh, I see.

13
00:02:41,370 --> 00:02:44,456
妈妈，不知道国王会不会来接我们？
Will the king of Siam come down
to meet us, Mother?

14
00:02:44,540 --> 00:02:47,584
我想当然不会来了，国王不会的，这有规矩
I hardly think so, dear.
Kings don't, as a rule.

15
00:02:53,382 --> 00:02:55,926
船头人手不足，快去
Come forward, lads.
They need help in the bow.

16
00:02:56,093 --> 00:02:57,511
快去那里
Get along there.

17
00:02:59,972 --> 00:03:01,098
那是皇室的船
That's the royal barge.

18
00:03:06,937 --> 00:03:09,231
国王来接我们了吗
The king is coming out to meet us.

19
00:03:09,398 --> 00:03:11,608
没有，是克拉拉贺
It's not the king, it's the Oklahoma.

20
00:03:11,859 --> 00:03:13,610
克拉拉贺是谁
Who is the kralahome?

21
00:03:13,735 --> 00:03:15,696
他是首相
A sort of a prime minister.

22
00:03:15,863 --> 00:03:18,740
应该是国王的助手吧
The king's right-hand man, you might say.

23
00:03:19,283 --> 00:03:22,244
让我看一下好吗，看一下
May I look? Please, may I see?

24
00:03:22,411 --> 00:03:23,871
夫人，我提醒你
Aye, laddie.

25
00:03:24,496 --> 00:03:28,834
最好对他小心点
Ma'am, if I might be allowed to offer
you a word of warning,

26
00:03:29,293 --> 00:03:32,588
因为他是一个很有权利的人
that man has power, and he can
use it for you or against you.

27
00:03:32,671 --> 00:03:35,465
跟他作对，后果不堪设想
You must stop worrying about me,
Captain Orton.

28
00:03:35,841 --> 00:03:38,594
我的事你尽管放心好了，船长
Sometimes I wonder if you know what
you're really facing.

29
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:41,180
我当然担心，一个英国女人
独自来到这个国家
An Englishwoman alone in a country like Siam.

30
00:03:41,263 --> 00:03:43,932
没关系，船长,我来这是工作的
It doesn't matter, captain.
I shall have work to do,

31
00:03:44,099 --> 00:03:46,894
再说国王又答应给
我和孩子提供住所
and the king has promised me
a house of my own.

32
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:50,564
如果亡夫地下有知的话,一定会赞成的
I'll have a place to bring up my boy
as his father would have wished.

33
00:03:50,981 --> 00:03:54,651
妈妈,你看,那位大臣竟然是赤裸的
Mother, look. The prime minister is naked!

34
00:03:54,735 --> 00:03:58,155
别好笑了，路易,怎么可能了
Oh, don't be ridiculous, Louis.
He can't be naked.

35
00:03:58,238 --> 00:03:59,740
他只是.
He's only...

36
00:04:00,657 --> 00:04:02,117
...半裸的
...half-naked.

37
00:04:04,119 --> 00:04:06,580
他们看起来有点吓人，妈妈
They look so cruel, Mother.

38
00:04:07,247 --> 00:04:09,750
爸爸不愿意看到我们害怕，是吗？
Father wouldn't have liked us to be afraid, would he?

39
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:13,253
路易，爸爸从来不愿看到我们害怕
No, Louis. Father would not have
liked us to be afraid.

40
00:04:13,420 --> 00:04:15,464
从来不
Not ever.

41
00:04:15,631 --> 00:04:17,591
妈妈，你什么都不怕吗
Doesn't anything ever frighten you?

42
00:04:17,758 --> 00:04:19,051
有时会的
Oh, yes, sometimes.

43
00:04:19,301 --> 00:04:21,470
你害怕的时候怎么办？
我会吹口哨
- What do you do?
- I whistle.

44
00:04:22,179 --> 00:04:24,306
那就是为什么你会吹口哨了
Oh, that's why you whistle.

45
00:04:25,098 --> 00:04:27,309
那就是我吹口哨的原因
That's why I whistle.

46
00:04:28,602 --> 00:04:31,063
当我感到害怕时
<i>Whenever I feel afraid</i>

47
00:04:31,146 --> 00:04:33,398
我就会挺起胸膛
<i>I hold my head erect</i>

48
00:04:33,732 --> 00:04:38,278
吹起高兴的乐曲，所以没人怀疑
<i>And whistle a happy tune,
So no one will suspect</i>

49
00:04:38,445 --> 00:04:40,864
我害怕
<i>I'm afraid</i>

50
00:04:41,323 --> 00:04:43,867
当我打颤时
<i>While shivering in my shoes</i>

51
00:04:44,034 --> 00:04:46,537
我就做个无畏的动作
<i>I strike a careless pose</i>

52
00:04:46,703 --> 00:04:48,830
吹高兴的乐曲
<i>And whistle a happy tune</i>

53
00:04:48,914 --> 00:04:52,960
没人知道我害怕
<i>And no one ever knows I'm afraid</i>

54
00:04:54,753 --> 00:04:57,214
口哨是很不可思议
<i>The result of this deception</i>

55
00:04:57,381 --> 00:04:59,675
的魔法
<i>is very strange to tell</i>

56
00:04:59,925 --> 00:05:02,803
连恐惧的对象
<i>For when I fool the people I fear</i>

57
00:05:02,886 --> 00:05:05,055
以及自己都被蒙骗
<i>I fool myself as well!</i>

58
00:05:05,430 --> 00:05:07,933
只要吹吹口哨
<i>I whistle a happy tune</i>

59
00:05:08,016 --> 00:05:10,602
在短时间内
<i>And every single time</i>

60
00:05:10,769 --> 00:05:13,188
就会被活泼的旋律
<i>The happiness in the tune</i>

61
00:05:13,355 --> 00:05:17,651
把恐惧冲散
<i>Convinces me that I'm not afraid.</i>

62
00:05:19,069 --> 00:05:21,280
要相信你很勇敢
<i>Make believe you're brave</i>

63
00:05:21,363 --> 00:05:23,866
这样勇气就会充满心胸
<i>And the trick will take you far.</i>

64
00:05:24,324 --> 00:05:26,660
你要勇敢
<i>You may be as brave</i>

65
00:05:26,743 --> 00:05:29,288
相信你能行
<i>As you make believe you are.</i>

66
00:05:35,127 --> 00:05:37,921
相信自己
<i>You may be as brave</i>

67
00:05:38,172 --> 00:05:41,341
你很勇敢
<i>As you make believe you are.</i>

68
00:05:46,013 --> 00:05:51,059
这是个好主意，妈妈，太好了
I think that's a very good idea,
Mother. A very good idea.

69
00:05:51,226 --> 00:05:54,229
对，这的确是个好主意
Yes, it is a good idea, isn't it?

70
00:05:54,396 --> 00:05:58,108
我不会再感到恐惧了，不会了，妈妈
I don't think I shall ever be afraid again.

71
00:05:58,358 --> 00:05:59,443
这就对了
Good.

72
00:05:59,610 --> 00:06:02,112
口哨是非常不可思议
<i>The result of this deception</i>

73
00:06:02,196 --> 00:06:04,823
的魔法
<i>ls very strange to tell</i>

74
00:06:04,990 --> 00:06:07,743
连恐惧的对象及自己
<i>For when I fool the people I fear</i>

75
00:06:07,826 --> 00:06:09,703
都会被蒙骗
<i>I fool myself as well!</i>

76
00:06:30,891 --> 00:06:32,684
这位是安娜李恩诺太太
This is Anna Halloweens.

77
00:06:32,768 --> 00:06:36,355
李恩诺太太，他是克拉拉贺首相
Mrs. Halloweens, may I present
His Excellency, the kralahome.

78
00:06:39,733 --> 00:06:44,571
请问阁下是皇室特聘的家庭教师吗
Sir, you are lady who will be
schoolmistress of the royal children?

79
00:06:44,738 --> 00:06:46,532
是的
他称你阁下
- Yes.
- He called you "sir."

80
00:06:46,698 --> 00:06:47,908
嘘，别说话
Hush, dear, hush.

81
00:06:48,075 --> 00:06:50,077
您在曼谷有朋友吗？
Have you friends in Bangkok?

82
00:06:50,244 --> 00:06:52,871
我不认识任何人
I know no one in Bangkok at all.

83
00:06:59,253 --> 00:07:03,131
首相问您结婚了没有
His Excellency wishes to know,
are you married, sir?

84
00:07:03,215 --> 00:07:04,591
我是个寡妇
I am a widow.

85
00:07:04,842 --> 00:07:08,428
您丈夫生前的
工作是什么呢
What manner of man,
your deceased husband?

86
00:07:08,595 --> 00:07:12,599
先夫是英国皇家陆军军官…
My husband was an officer
of Her Majesty's Army in...

87
00:07:14,184 --> 00:07:16,019
我想问一下，
那些事…
Tell your master his business with me

88
00:07:16,103 --> 00:07:18,438
跟我当家庭教师有什么关系吗
is as schoolteacher to the royal children.

89
00:07:18,772 --> 00:07:21,358
我希望不要探索我的隐私
He has no right to pry
into my personal affairs.

90
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:23,110
他不是这个意思，船长
He hasn't, Captain Orton.

91
00:07:30,659 --> 00:07:32,202
我不喜欢这个人
I don't like that man.

92
00:07:32,369 --> 00:07:36,498
你在这的期间最好别独树一帜，明白吗？
In foreign country is best
you like everyone until you leave.

93
00:07:36,665 --> 00:07:40,043
你会说英语，竟然说不会
You might at least have told us
you speak English, Your Excellency.

94
00:07:40,210 --> 00:07:44,464
我不许家庭教师什么都知道
It is not necessary for schoolteacher
to know everything at once.

95
00:07:44,715 --> 00:07:46,300
你现在跟我来
You come with me now.

96
00:07:46,466 --> 00:07:49,136
行李待会儿运到皇宫去
Your baggages shall be carried
to palace later.

97
00:07:49,303 --> 00:07:53,515
请等一下，我并不住在那
Just a minute. Not the palace.
I am not living in the palace.

98
00:07:53,682 --> 00:07:56,643
谁说的
国王
- Who say?
- The king say... Says.

99
00:07:56,894 --> 00:07:59,938
在他的信里答应每月给我20磅的薪水
In his letter of agreement,
he promised me 20￡ a month

100
00:08:00,147 --> 00:08:02,774
并在皇宫外给我安排了住的地方
and a house of my own
outside the palace walls.

101
00:08:03,108 --> 00:08:05,944
国王已经不记得他的承诺了
King do not always remember
what he promise.

102
00:08:06,028 --> 00:08:08,322
那就请你提醒他好了
Then you will have to remind him.

103
00:08:08,405 --> 00:08:12,075
我若提醒.会引起他的圣怒
If I tell king he break this promise,
I will make anger in him.

104
00:08:12,242 --> 00:08:16,622
我不想为了这些无聊的事引起不快
I think is better if king's anger
reserved for more important matters.

105
00:08:16,788 --> 00:08:20,167
好啊，如果你不敢告诉他的话
Very well, then. If you are
afraid to tell him, I will.

106
00:08:20,250 --> 00:08:23,170
我是不是要见他，要视情况而定了
I should like to see him at once,
while there's time for me

107
00:08:23,253 --> 00:08:25,130
或许我应该立刻返回英国
to return to England on this boat.

108
00:08:25,422 --> 00:08:27,674
国王正忙呢
阁下
- King very busy now.
- Your Excellency,

109
00:08:27,841 --> 00:08:30,677
我并不想占用他很多时间
all I want is
a few minutes' audience with him.

110
00:08:30,844 --> 00:08:33,347
我来这是工作的，但也不会放弃自己的权利
I have come here to work
and I intend to work,

111
00:08:33,514 --> 00:08:37,017
我要争取得到我应得的一切
but I shall take nothing less
than I have been promised.

112
00:08:37,184 --> 00:08:39,186
你就这样对国王说话吗？
You will tell king this?

113
00:08:39,978 --> 00:08:41,855
我会的
I will tell king this.

114
00:08:42,022 --> 00:08:45,484
这将是一场有趣的晋见
It should be very interesting meeting.

115
00:08:45,651 --> 00:08:47,110
来吧
You come now!

116
00:08:48,445 --> 00:08:49,988
如果你改变主意
If you change your mind...

117
00:08:50,072 --> 00:08:53,033
再见，船长，谢谢你的照顾
Goodbye, Captain Orton,
and thank you for everything.

118
00:08:53,116 --> 00:08:54,201
祝你好运，夫人
Good luck, ma'am.

119
00:08:54,284 --> 00:08:56,119
再见，船长
再见孩子
- Goodbye, captain.
- Goodbye, laddie.

120
00:08:56,203 --> 00:08:58,413
要好好照顾你的妈妈
Take good care of your mother, now.

121
00:10:52,110 --> 00:10:54,655
国王今天心情不好
King in bad spirit today.

122
00:10:54,947 --> 00:10:58,075
还是改天再来吧
Suggest schoolteacher wait for better day.

123
00:10:58,242 --> 00:11:01,787
我也一样心情不好，先生
My spirit is just as bad, Your Excellency.
I cannot wait.

124
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:34,695
那个男的是缅甸皇室的使者
Man is Lun Tha,
emissary from court of Burma.

125
00:11:34,862 --> 00:11:38,532
那个女的是缅甸皇太子送来的礼物
He bring present to king
from prince of Burma.

126
00:11:38,699 --> 00:11:41,034
她名字叫达布提
Her name is Tuptim.

127
00:11:41,201 --> 00:11:43,787
那个女孩是供品
Why, that girl is a present?

128
00:11:44,538 --> 00:11:45,789
送给国王的
For king.

129
00:12:18,071 --> 00:12:20,908
国王收下她了
King is pleased with her.

130
00:12:32,503 --> 00:12:35,839
对不起，
国王上朝的时间到此结束
Sorry. King has concluded audience.

131
00:12:36,089 --> 00:12:38,217
你是说我无法晋见国王
Well, you mean I cannot see him?

132
00:12:38,383 --> 00:12:40,093
下次吧
Not today.

133
00:12:41,470 --> 00:12:43,680
路易，跟我来
Louis, come with me.

134
00:12:48,393 --> 00:12:50,020
你不能这样
You cannot do this!

135
00:12:56,401 --> 00:12:58,237
国王陛下
你是谁
- Your Majesty.
- Who, who, who?

136
00:12:58,403 --> 00:13:01,406
他是请来教英语的家庭教师
Your Majesty, is new English schoolteacher.

137
00:13:01,573 --> 00:13:03,700
安娜女士和她的儿子
Mrs. Anna Halloweens and son.

138
00:13:03,867 --> 00:13:06,036
他叫路易
Louis Halloweens.

139
00:13:07,955 --> 00:13:10,082
你是家庭教师
You are schoolteacher?

140
00:13:10,249 --> 00:13:14,711
是的，陛下，但在工作之前
我要弄清楚一件事
Yes, Your Majesty. But before I start
my work here, there is one point...

141
00:13:14,878 --> 00:13:17,923
我是为了让泰国更现代化…
You are part of general plan I have
for bringing to Siam

142
00:13:18,090 --> 00:13:20,425
所以才找你来
what is good in Western culture.

143
00:13:20,592 --> 00:13:24,221
而且我还引进了印刷机
Already I have bring printing press here
for printing.

144
00:13:24,388 --> 00:13:26,807
我知道，陛下
你怎么知道的
- Yes, I know, Your Majesty.
- How you know?

145
00:13:27,558 --> 00:13:32,479
在签约之前，我已经将所有的事情都调查过了
Before I signed our agreement, I found out
about your ambitions for Siam.

146
00:13:37,818 --> 00:13:39,736
你有多大？
How old shall you be?

147
00:13:40,279 --> 00:13:43,073
你有自信教科学方面的知识吗
You do not look like
scientific person for teaching.

148
00:13:43,240 --> 00:13:44,741
你到底几岁了
How old shall you be?

149
00:13:45,576 --> 00:13:48,495
我有150岁，陛下
I am 150 years old, Your Majesty.

150
00:13:50,998 --> 00:13:52,791
你是哪年生的
In what year were you borned?

151
00:13:54,126 --> 00:13:57,921
我是1712年
In 1712, Your Majesty.

152
00:14:02,426 --> 00:14:05,637
你结婚多久了
How many years
shall you have been married?

153
00:14:05,804 --> 00:14:07,973
有几年了
Several, Your Majesty.

154
00:14:12,769 --> 00:14:15,272
你有多少孙子
How many grandchildren
shall you have by now?

155
00:14:15,439 --> 00:14:17,608
告诉我，有多少，
有多少
How many, how many, how many?

156
00:14:17,774 --> 00:14:19,026
你答不出来了吧
You do not answer fast.

157
00:14:19,109 --> 00:14:21,069
我赢了，我赢了
I make better question
than she make answer.

158
00:14:27,492 --> 00:14:30,120
你不怕国王
You are not afraid of king.

159
00:14:30,954 --> 00:14:35,292
对，科学精神是不允许有恐惧感的
Not to be afraid is good thing
in scientific mind.

160
00:14:35,459 --> 00:14:38,504
我想也许.
I think maybe

161
00:14:38,795 --> 00:14:41,006
你能够当个好老师
you make very good schoolteaching.

162
00:14:41,173 --> 00:14:42,216
来吧
Come.

163
00:14:57,856 --> 00:14:59,733
他们都是我的妃子
A few of my wives.

164
00:14:59,900 --> 00:15:02,903
他们都很美丽却没有学识
They have beauty
but not gift for knowledge.

165
00:15:03,070 --> 00:15:06,657
我因为外交事务繁忙，所以没时间管教育
I have no time for teaching,
being busy with foreign affairs

166
00:15:06,865 --> 00:15:08,825
和一些其他的事情
and other situations.

167
00:15:09,701 --> 00:15:13,163
她是张妃，是这里的大太太
I may present Lady Thiang, head wife.

168
00:15:15,082 --> 00:15:19,837
遥远的地方有个富裕的国度
<i>There is a happy land
far, far away</i>

169
00:15:20,003 --> 00:15:22,673
到处充满了圣者的
<i>Where saints in glory stand</i>

170
00:15:22,798 --> 00:15:26,009
耀眼国度
<i>Bright, bright as day.</i>

171
00:15:27,010 --> 00:15:31,181
"最初是神创造了天与地"
"In the beginning, God
created the heaven and the earth."

172
00:15:31,348 --> 00:15:32,850
是传教士教我的
Missionary.

173
00:15:33,058 --> 00:15:35,853
传教士教你英语了
Oh, a missionary taught you English.

174
00:15:35,978 --> 00:15:38,939
是的
Yes, sir. Missionary.

175
00:15:39,273 --> 00:15:41,191
我也有儿子
跟他差不多大
I have boy too.

176
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:45,737
他的名字是裘雷达汗皇太子
Crown Prince Chowfa Chulalongkorn,
heir to throne.

177
00:15:45,904 --> 00:15:48,115
你来当她的助手…
You help Madam Halloweens
with schoolteaching

178
00:15:48,198 --> 00:15:51,493
而且要好好的学习英语
and she in turn shall teach you
the better English.

179
00:15:53,704 --> 00:15:56,290
她很感谢我的仁慈安排
She is very grateful to me for my kindness.

180
00:15:56,456 --> 00:16:00,878
张妃，你去带孩子们，来见见老师
Lady Thiang, have children prepare
for presentation to schoolteacher.

181
00:16:02,379 --> 00:16:05,007
这个，陛下，我想先谈谈和约问题
Speaking of teaching, Your Majesty,
in our agreement...

182
00:16:05,090 --> 00:16:07,676
孙妃，达拉妃，碧亚妃
Lady Son Klin, Lady Talap, Lady Piam.

183
00:16:08,010 --> 00:16:11,930
而这位女孩是由缅甸送来的
And this girl is present to me
from a Burma prince.

184
00:16:12,222 --> 00:16:13,307
刚刚送来
She just arrived.

185
00:16:13,557 --> 00:16:15,058
你好，夫人
Good day, madam.

186
00:16:15,392 --> 00:16:19,980
我叫达布提，我也会说英语
My name is Tuptim. I already speak English.

187
00:16:20,314 --> 00:16:22,566
你说的非常好
And very nicely too.

188
00:16:22,733 --> 00:16:25,235
我有个更好的主意
I think I have fine idea.

189
00:16:25,402 --> 00:16:28,655
在教孩子之余，顺便教教这些妃子们
In addition to children, you will also teach
those of my wives

190
00:16:28,739 --> 00:16:30,574
教她们…科学知识
as have sense enough for learning.

191
00:16:30,741 --> 00:16:33,619
先进国家的女性
Siam to be very modern, scientific country.

192
00:16:33,785 --> 00:16:35,662
都会说英语
Everybody speaking the English.

193
00:16:35,996 --> 00:16:40,375
但是国王陛下，我记得契约上没写要教妃子
Your Majesty, it is not in our agreement
that I teach your wives too.

194
00:16:40,459 --> 00:16:44,588
另外你可以帮我写写外交文件
Also, I will allow you to help me
in my foreign correspondence.

195
00:16:44,755 --> 00:16:47,591
我很乐意为你效劳
I shall be perfectly happy to help you
in any way I can

196
00:16:47,758 --> 00:16:51,261
但是我想先谈谈房子的事情
provided we can clear up
this one little matter of the house.

197
00:16:51,428 --> 00:16:52,763
房子？
House?

198
00:16:53,096 --> 00:16:54,264
房子？什么房子
House? What house?

199
00:16:54,431 --> 00:16:58,185
我记得你答应在皇宫旁边盖间房子给我的
My house, Your Majesty. The one
you promised me, adjoining the palace.

200
00:16:58,352 --> 00:17:01,438
最好是住在皇宫里
It is a pleasure that you
shall live in palace.

201
00:17:01,647 --> 00:17:04,316
在皇宫里教书，你就住在这
You teach in palace,
and you shall live in palace.

202
00:17:04,983 --> 00:17:09,029
从这里可以看到很多美丽的景色
Will have nice apartment.
Can look out, see many things.

203
00:17:09,112 --> 00:17:11,532
我当然知道看到什么东西了
Oh, yes, I'm sure we could see many things,

204
00:17:11,615 --> 00:17:15,994
那就是铁栏杆，卫兵，等等等等
such as iron bars, guards at the doors,
et cetera, et cetera.

205
00:17:17,287 --> 00:17:19,122
什么是等等
What is this "et cetera"?

206
00:17:21,458 --> 00:17:25,170
那是表示还有其他相似东西的意思
Well, it means "and all the rest
and so forth," Your Majesty.

207
00:17:27,881 --> 00:17:29,216
来见见我的孩子们
You will meet my children.

208
00:17:29,299 --> 00:17:32,386
国王陛下，如果房子的问题没谈妥的话
I'm sorry, Your Majesty,
but if there is to be no house,

209
00:17:32,469 --> 00:17:34,763
我想搭原来的船返回英国
I shall have to get back to the boat.

210
00:17:34,847 --> 00:17:38,183
别再说了，见见我的孩子们
You will stand here and meet royal children.

211
00:17:43,522 --> 00:17:45,566
遵命，陛下
Very well, Your Majesty.

212
00:17:46,817 --> 00:17:49,069
但请快点
But there isn't much time.

213
00:17:54,575 --> 00:17:57,494
王子和公主进来吧
The royal princes and princesses.

214
00:21:28,372 --> 00:21:29,706
来
Well, well, well?

215
00:21:58,735 --> 00:22:02,489
现在你还要解决房子的问题
Schoolteacher has graciously
changed her mind and shall live in palace.

216
00:22:02,656 --> 00:22:05,409
房子迟些再说，陛下
For the time being, Your Majesty.

217
00:22:05,617 --> 00:22:07,744
这些都是你要教的
These are the children you shall teach.

218
00:22:07,911 --> 00:22:10,747
改天我让你见见其他的孩子
Someday shall allow you
to meet my others.

219
00:22:10,914 --> 00:22:12,791
还有其他的孩子？
More, Your Majesty?

220
00:22:12,958 --> 00:22:15,586
还有些不住在宫里的
Children of wives not in favor with king.

221
00:22:15,669 --> 00:22:17,629
一共是67个
Sixty-seven, I think.

222
00:22:17,754 --> 00:22:18,922
67个
Oh.

223
00:22:24,303 --> 00:22:25,345
不
Hmm.

224
00:22:34,438 --> 00:22:38,859
不，别这样，别乱动行李箱
No! Oh, ladies, please. Don't open that, no.

225
00:22:39,026 --> 00:22:42,779
哦，我的天，请回你们自己房间去
Oh, my goodness! Oh, won't you all
go back to your rooms?

226
00:22:43,071 --> 00:22:45,282
张妃，请叫她们别这样
Lady Thiang, will you please
ask them to leave?

227
00:22:45,365 --> 00:22:47,451
我有自己的隐私
I must have some privacy.

228
00:22:58,962 --> 00:23:01,465
天哪，她们到底想干什么
Good heavens!
What are they trying to do to me?

229
00:23:01,757 --> 00:23:06,053
他们想知道你的身体是否也像裙子的形状
Sir, they think you wear dress like that
because you shaped like that.

230
00:23:06,136 --> 00:23:08,388
哦，当然不是
Well, I most certainly am not.

231
00:23:11,475 --> 00:23:13,810
他们只是想了解，阁下
你的孩子呢，他在哪
They wish to know, sir,
if they may see the boy?

232
00:23:13,977 --> 00:23:16,230
对不起，他正在睡觉
I'm sorry, Lady Thiang, he is asleep.

233
00:23:16,396 --> 00:23:20,484
请告诉我为什么称我为阁下
Please, do tell me.
Why do you keep calling me sir?

234
00:23:20,651 --> 00:23:24,905
因为你不是普通的女人
Because you scientific,
not lowly like woman.

235
00:23:25,322 --> 00:23:28,992
难道女人比男人低一等吗
But do you all think
that women are more lowly than men?

236
00:23:32,412 --> 00:23:34,331
那是非常错误的观点
Well, I certainly do not.

237
00:23:34,498 --> 00:23:38,502
要是让国王听到了会大发雷霆的
Please, sir, do not tell king.
Make king angry.

238
00:23:38,669 --> 00:23:41,672
国王陛下也需要接受教育才行
Perhaps it's time somebody did tell him
a thing or two.

239
00:23:41,839 --> 00:23:43,257
安娜夫人
Mrs. Anna?

240
00:23:43,674 --> 00:23:47,594
请问你有没有英文书借给我看
Please, you have some English books
I can read?

241
00:23:47,678 --> 00:23:51,390
当然有,可是要等到行李箱打开才行
Yes, of course, my dear,
but they're not unpacked yet.

242
00:23:58,021 --> 00:24:00,524
她们笑她是因为她很愚蠢
They laugh at her
because she is foolish child.

243
00:24:00,899 --> 00:24:04,611
她能在皇宫伺候国王，但并不快乐
She has come to live in palace of king
and yet she is unhappy.

244
00:24:04,695 --> 00:24:07,155
毕竟，她在这件事上别无选择
After all, she had no choice in the matter.

245
00:24:07,239 --> 00:24:09,533
我想她一定是思念自己的故乡
Perhaps she is homesick.

246
00:24:13,579 --> 00:24:16,915
不是思念故乡
Is not homesickness that make me sad,
Mrs. Anna.

247
00:24:17,082 --> 00:24:19,877
而是思念我无法再见到的人
Is love for one I shall never see again.

248
00:24:20,043 --> 00:24:21,253
哦，可怜的孩子
Oh, poor child.

249
00:24:21,420 --> 00:24:25,048
他就是带我来的使者伦塔
He is Lun Tha,
who was chosen to bring me here.

250
00:24:25,215 --> 00:24:28,218
我们都极力克制过了…
We tried so hard
not to have love for each other

251
00:24:28,385 --> 00:24:30,929
但还是情不自禁的双双堕入了情网
but we could not help ourselves.

252
00:24:31,221 --> 00:24:33,307
我们试过了
We did try, Mrs. Anna.

253
00:24:33,473 --> 00:24:37,936
思念不是说停就能停下来的
It isn't easy to stop loving a man
if he's the man you want.

254
00:24:38,103 --> 00:24:41,106
并不是不见就能割断思念之情
Even if you know
you will never see him again.

255
00:24:41,982 --> 00:24:43,442
我知道
I know.

256
00:24:44,067 --> 00:24:47,404
我也非常思念我的先夫
I was very much in love with my husband.

257
00:24:53,243 --> 00:24:55,287
请你们放回原处好吗
Please ask them to put that down.

258
00:24:55,454 --> 00:24:58,624
大家想知道他是谁
They wish to know, sir, who is man?

259
00:24:59,833 --> 00:25:03,337
他就是我死去的丈夫汤姆
That was my husband, Tom.

260
00:25:05,756 --> 00:25:07,216
汤姆
- Tom.
- Mm-hmm.

261
00:25:07,299 --> 00:25:09,176
他长的很帅
He was pretty in face.

262
00:25:09,343 --> 00:25:13,639
是啊，他长的非常英俊
Oh, dear, yes, he was. Very pretty in face.

263
00:25:16,099 --> 00:25:19,937
每当我想起他
<i>When I think of Tom</i>

264
00:25:20,145 --> 00:25:22,773
就禁不住想那一夜
<i>I think about a night</i>

265
00:25:22,856 --> 00:25:26,026
大地弥漫着夏日的气息
<i>When the earth smelled of summer</i>

266
00:25:26,109 --> 00:25:29,154
云朵在天空漂浮
<i>And the sky was streaked with white</i>

267
00:25:29,321 --> 00:25:32,950
轻柔的雾气弥漫
<i>And the soft mist of England</i>

268
00:25:33,033 --> 00:25:35,994
着英格兰小山冈
<i>Was sleeping on a hill,</i>

269
00:25:36,119 --> 00:25:40,541
这些我都记得
<i>I remember this</i>

270
00:25:41,166 --> 00:25:47,339
永远记得
<i>And I always will.</i>

271
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:53,053
我深知我俩的爱情
<i>There are new lovers now</i>

272
00:25:53,136 --> 00:25:56,932
见证在寂静山岗
<i>On the same silent hill</i>

273
00:25:57,140 --> 00:26:02,604
常常浮现在我的脑海
<i>Looking on the same blue sea,</i>

274
00:26:03,397 --> 00:26:07,234
汤姆和我永远
<i>And I know Tom and I</i>

275
00:26:07,317 --> 00:26:10,988
是大地的一分子
<i>are a part of them all,</i>

276
00:26:11,154 --> 00:26:16,326
而他们也是汤姆的一分子
<i>And they're all a part of Tom</i>

277
00:26:17,494 --> 00:26:23,083
我也是
<i>and me.</i>

278
00:26:25,711 --> 00:26:31,383
年轻的爱人们，无论你是谁
<i>Hello, young lovers, whoever you are,</i>

279
00:26:31,550 --> 00:26:37,431
希望你们一切顺利
<i>I hope your troubles are few.</i>

280
00:26:38,223 --> 00:26:45,230
我的祝愿伴你度过今宵
<i>All my good wishes go with you tonight.</i>

281
00:26:46,023 --> 00:26:50,986
我也像你们一样爱过
<i>I've been in love like you.</i>

282
00:26:51,069 --> 00:26:53,947
提起勇气
<i>Be brave, young lovers,</i>

283
00:26:54,031 --> 00:26:56,700
抓住幸运之星
<i>and follow your star,</i>

284
00:26:57,117 --> 00:27:02,539
提起勇气抓住真爱
<i>Be brave and faithful and true,</i>

285
00:27:03,582 --> 00:27:06,210
紧紧相拥
<i>Cling very close</i>

286
00:27:06,293 --> 00:27:10,797
在日升之前
<i>to each other tonight.</i>

287
00:27:11,215 --> 00:27:16,345
我也像你们一样爱过
<i>I've been in love like you.</i>

288
00:27:16,637 --> 00:27:21,600
我知道脚上长翅膀
是什么样的感觉
<i>I know how it feels
to have wings on your heels</i>

289
00:27:21,767 --> 00:27:26,605
在梦中徘徊散步
<i>And to fly down a street in a trance.</i>

290
00:27:26,772 --> 00:27:32,069
你们相识在偶然
<i>You fly down a street
on the chance that you'll meet,</i>

291
00:27:32,569 --> 00:27:34,655
你们相识
<i>And you meet</i>

292
00:27:35,405 --> 00:27:41,119
真的不是意外
<i>not really by chance.</i>

293
00:27:42,454 --> 00:27:48,794
无论你们做了什么，
年轻的爱人们，别哭
<i>Don't cw, young lovers whatever you do</i>

294
00:27:49,086 --> 00:27:54,591
别因为我孤独而为我哭泣
<i>Don't cry because I'm alone,</i>

295
00:27:56,009 --> 00:27:58,804
我所有的记忆让我
<i>All of my mem'ries</i>

296
00:27:58,887 --> 00:28:03,433
今晚很快乐
<i>are happy tonight,</i>

297
00:28:03,976 --> 00:28:09,147
我曾经有过自己的爱
<i>I've had a love of my own,</i>

298
00:28:09,606 --> 00:28:14,027
我曾经有过自己的爱
<i>I've had a love of my own,</i>

299
00:28:14,111 --> 00:28:17,281
像你们一样
<i>like yours,</i>

300
00:28:17,489 --> 00:28:21,076
我曾经有过
<i>I've had a love</i>

301
00:28:21,910 --> 00:28:28,917
自己的爱
<i>of my own.</i>

302
00:28:38,969 --> 00:28:44,850
快乐的殿堂
<i>Be it pleasures and palaces,</i>

303
00:28:45,017 --> 00:28:49,855
任我们遨游
<i>Though we may roam,</i>

304
00:28:50,314 --> 00:28:55,861
曾经如此卑微
<i>Be it ever so humble,</i>

305
00:28:56,028 --> 00:29:01,533
如家般温暖
<i>There's no place like home.</i>

306
00:29:01,992 --> 00:29:06,830
天空的魅力
<i>A charm from the skies</i>

307
00:29:07,164 --> 00:29:12,002
我们共同分享
<i>Seems to hallow us there,</i>

308
00:29:12,336 --> 00:29:14,671
父皇，我上学快迟到了
- Father, I'll be late for school!
- You wait.

309
00:29:14,838 --> 00:29:18,175
你昨天在学校学过什么谚语…
You are pleased to recite proverb
you learn yesterday

310
00:29:18,425 --> 00:29:21,762
应该写过十二遍了吧
and writing down 12 times in copybook.

311
00:29:21,887 --> 00:29:23,555
"不管在东方--
"A thought for the day:

312
00:29:23,805 --> 00:29:25,682
还是西方"
East or west,

313
00:29:25,891 --> 00:29:27,935
没有比家更舒适之处"
home is best."

314
00:29:28,101 --> 00:29:31,146
东方、西方、家，又提到了房子
"East, west, home, best," means house!

315
00:29:31,230 --> 00:29:34,483
"房子仅次于名誉…"
"A man's house is only less dear to him
than his honor."

316
00:29:34,650 --> 00:29:38,278
每天总是提到房子的事
Every day, month after week,
something about house.

317
00:29:38,529 --> 00:29:40,864
除了房子你还学到别的事吗
Are my children to be taught nothing more?

318
00:29:41,031 --> 00:29:42,866
昨天她说…
Yesterday we are taught

319
00:29:43,116 --> 00:29:45,452
地球像球一样的圆
that the world is a round ball

320
00:29:45,702 --> 00:29:49,206
还会旋转呢…
which spins on an invisible stick
through its middle.

321
00:29:49,373 --> 00:29:53,335
可是，地球应该在龟背上才对
Everyone knows
the world rides on the back of a turtle

322
00:29:53,418 --> 00:29:55,295
这样才会安全
who keeps it from running into the stars.

323
00:29:55,379 --> 00:29:58,257
但是接受己见不一定是对的…
How can it be
that everyone knows one thing

324
00:29:58,340 --> 00:30:00,968
顽固的人总是犯下错？
if many people believe another thing?

325
00:30:01,468 --> 00:30:03,512
那真相是什么呢
Then which is true?

326
00:30:05,305 --> 00:30:07,099
我相信地球应该是…
The world is ball

327
00:30:07,266 --> 00:30:08,851
圆的并且会旋转
with stick through it.

328
00:30:09,101 --> 00:30:10,143
我相信
I believe.

329
00:30:10,310 --> 00:30:11,728
你相信？
You believe?

330
00:30:11,895 --> 00:30:14,147
所以你无所不知才行
Does that mean that you do not know?

331
00:30:14,314 --> 00:30:17,150
没错，你必须知道，因为你要成为国王
But you must know, because you are king.

332
00:30:17,234 --> 00:30:18,402
没错
Good.

333
00:30:18,569 --> 00:30:21,238
有天你也会当上国王的
Someday you too will be king,

334
00:30:21,488 --> 00:30:23,574
那时你就知道所有的事
and you too will know everything.

335
00:30:23,949 --> 00:30:25,659
我怎么才能学习到呢
But how do I learn?

336
00:30:25,868 --> 00:30:27,911
怎样才能无所不知呢
And when do I know that I know everything?

337
00:30:31,582 --> 00:30:33,542
当你成为国王的时候
When you are king.

338
00:30:37,212 --> 00:30:39,715
当你成为国王的时候
When you are king.

339
00:30:41,592 --> 00:30:43,427
可我不知道
But I do not know.

340
00:30:45,012 --> 00:30:48,182
我没有一件事确定…
In my head are many facts,
but I am not sure.

341
00:30:49,391 --> 00:30:52,394
我该如何告诉她.
What to tell a growing son?

342
00:30:53,520 --> 00:30:56,481
如何正确对待政治和子民呢
How to bring truth and justice
to my people?

343
00:31:01,195 --> 00:31:02,946
当我是个孩子时
<i>When I was a boy,</i>

344
00:31:03,780 --> 00:31:05,490
世界比现在还灿烂
<i>World was better spot,</i>

345
00:31:06,241 --> 00:31:08,118
什么都是
<i>What was so was so,</i>

346
00:31:08,702 --> 00:31:10,329
黑白分明
