00:42:59,329 --> 00:43:01,081
你们为什么不相信
Who does not believe this?

532
00:43:01,248 --> 00:43:03,834
陛下，因为他们没有亲眼见过
Well, after all, they've never seen it.

533
00:43:04,042 --> 00:43:06,003
没有见过
Never seen?

534
00:43:06,170 --> 00:43:10,465
如果只相信见过的事物，就不需要学校了
If they believe only what they see,
why do we have schoolroom? Rise!

535
00:43:12,342 --> 00:43:15,512
站起来，要相信老师的话…
Never let me hear
of not believing schoolteacher

536
00:43:16,346 --> 00:43:20,100
她是我专程从英国请来的…
whom I have bring here at high expense.

537
00:43:21,810 --> 00:43:23,478
每个月要付20磅
Twenty pounds each month.

538
00:43:25,272 --> 00:43:27,900
20英镑
Twenty English pounds.

539
00:43:28,275 --> 00:43:29,860
坐下
Sterling!

540
00:43:30,444 --> 00:43:31,778
站起来
Rise!

541
00:43:33,739 --> 00:43:34,781
这是为你们个人.
I command all of you

542
00:43:34,865 --> 00:43:38,660
和国家着想…
to make most of this opportunity
for expensive education.

543
00:43:39,286 --> 00:43:41,955
所以别浪费了这么贵的上课费…
For sake of selves and country.

544
00:43:42,456 --> 00:43:44,374
为了自己也是为了国家
Furthermore, it is...

545
00:43:44,541 --> 00:43:47,294
什么，什么，不是我给你的书吧
What, what, what?
This is not study book I have provide.

546
00:43:47,878 --> 00:43:50,047
不，陛下，是我的书
No, Your Majesty, it's one of mine.

547
00:43:50,214 --> 00:43:52,883
我给她的
那本书是叫什么
- I gave it to Tuptim.
- The name! You tell me!

548
00:43:53,383 --> 00:43:56,220
是汤姆叔叔的小屋
<i>Is calledThe Small House of Uncle Thomas.</i>

549
00:43:56,386 --> 00:43:59,681
作者是美国的斯陀夫人
ls by American lady, Harriet Beecher Stowe.

550
00:44:00,557 --> 00:44:02,309
一个女人也可以写书？
A woman has written a book?

551
00:44:02,476 --> 00:44:05,646
汤姆叔叔的小屋，是本很优秀的作品
<i>Uncle</i> Tom's <i>Cabin.</i>
A wonderful book, Your Majesty.

552
00:44:05,812 --> 00:44:08,565
是批评美奴隶制的
All about the evils of slavery in America.

553
00:44:08,732 --> 00:44:11,735
林肯先生也是反对派的
President Lincoln of America
against slavery, no?

554
00:44:11,902 --> 00:44:13,570
没错，陛下
Very definitely, Your Majesty.

555
00:44:13,779 --> 00:44:15,239
我也不喜欢
Me too.

556
00:44:15,405 --> 00:44:17,783
奴隶制很不好
Slavery very bad thing.

557
00:44:19,117 --> 00:44:23,247
林肯为了解放奴隶而战，仍被人们喝彩
Mr. Lincoln is fighting a war,
even now, to set the slaves free.

558
00:44:23,789 --> 00:44:25,249
你认为他很了不起
You admire him for this?

559
00:44:25,415 --> 00:44:26,959
是的，陛下
Very much, Your Majesty.

560
00:44:27,125 --> 00:44:29,837
他不怕吃苦.
He seems to be a fine man
who has studied hard

561
00:44:29,920 --> 00:44:31,880
独自学习
and educated himself.

562
00:44:32,130 --> 00:44:34,925
这点您就比他差点了
In that, he is not unlike yourself.

563
00:44:39,137 --> 00:44:42,516
你认为他打赢之后赢得了总统的职位？
Shall Mr. Lincoln be winning this war
he is fighting at present?

564
00:44:42,766 --> 00:44:44,351
我不这么认为
No one knows, really.

565
00:44:44,434 --> 00:44:48,105
他有足够的枪和大象来运输
Does he have enough guns and elephants
for transporting same?

566
00:44:48,647 --> 00:44:52,442
在美国是没有大象的，陛下
I don't think they have elephants
in America, Your Majesty.

567
00:44:52,609 --> 00:44:54,528
没有大象？没有
- No elephants?
- No.

568
00:44:54,945 --> 00:44:56,697
那他一定输定了
No wonder he's not winning war.

569
00:44:58,615 --> 00:45:01,201
好了，孩子们，该上课了
All right, children, you may be seated now.

570
00:45:06,415 --> 00:45:09,084
安娜夫人
什么事，裘雷拉汗
- Mrs. Anna?
- Yes, Your Highness?

571
00:45:09,459 --> 00:45:11,336
我不明白
I do not understand

572
00:45:11,420 --> 00:45:14,923
当主人解放奴隶之后…那些奴隶该怎么办呢
how slaves can be set free
if their masters wish to keep them.

573
00:45:15,799 --> 00:45:18,302
必要时要执行法律
It's done by the passing of a law

574
00:45:18,385 --> 00:45:20,971
强制性执行
and by the enforcing of that law,
if necessary.

575
00:45:21,555 --> 00:45:22,890
但是如果我有奴隶
But my slaves

576
00:45:22,973 --> 00:45:24,892
或者是父皇有奴隶…
and the slaves of my father...

577
00:45:24,975 --> 00:45:28,312
而我们又反对这种法律该怎么办呢
Suppose there was such a law in Siam
and we did not want it so?

578
00:45:28,645 --> 00:45:33,400
有时应该抑制欲望选择正确的
Sometimes things can't be just
a question of what we want, Highness,

579
00:45:33,483 --> 00:45:34,902
这才是真正的为王之道
but of what is right.

580
00:45:45,162 --> 00:45:46,163
对的
Ha.

581
00:45:49,917 --> 00:45:53,253
好了，现在你们可以休息吃午饭了
I think perhaps we had better call
recess until after luncheon.

582
00:45:53,337 --> 00:45:54,796
你们可以回去
You may be excused.

583
00:46:16,151 --> 00:46:19,279
年轻的皇太子会
Young prince has healthy respect

584
00:46:19,363 --> 00:46:21,448
更认真地考虑人民的事
for ways of his own people.

585
00:46:21,532 --> 00:46:23,909
有时甚至会超过国王
Sometimes more than king.

586
00:46:23,992 --> 00:46:28,205
他是位思想很细致
Prince Chulalongkorn is a fine boy
with a keen and probing mind.

587
00:46:29,540 --> 00:46:31,875
有强烈探索心的孩子
But he still has much to learn,
Your Excellency.

588
00:46:33,377 --> 00:46:35,712
今后的教育，对他有重要的作用.
What is important for him to learn

589
00:46:35,796 --> 00:46:38,257
不，我不认为这个教室对他有作用
I do not think he'll find
in this classroom.

590
00:46:38,882 --> 00:46:42,386
这么说你是反对我来这教书了
I'm fully aware that you do not
approve of my coming to Siam.

591
00:46:42,469 --> 00:46:45,472
你怎么看不出来呢
Why are you so blind?
Have you no eyes to see?

592
00:46:45,556 --> 00:46:48,141
国王是向不可能挑战
King tries impossible task

593
00:46:48,225 --> 00:46:51,270
讲究科学，讲究现代化
wishing to be scientific man
who learn all modern things.

594
00:46:51,436 --> 00:46:53,438
我认为他有崇高的理想
I think it a fine ambition.

595
00:46:53,522 --> 00:46:56,984
继承了父王的强大意志，不可能轻易改变
Inside him is strong king like
his father, who cannot change.

596
00:46:57,359 --> 00:47:01,029
如果过于勉强导致灭亡
He will only tear himself in two, trying
to be something he can never be.

597
00:47:01,405 --> 00:47:03,323
就得不偿失了
Of course he can never be

598
00:47:03,407 --> 00:47:06,076
当然他需要身边的人协助,你说不是吗
if those closest to him
are unwilling to help him.

599
00:47:06,159 --> 00:47:08,370
你根本不之道国王在想什么,你又能做些什么
You do not know king
as well as you think you do.

600
00:47:09,872 --> 00:47:12,457
你永远相信你有过人的智慧
You believe you have
great influence over him.

601
00:47:12,541 --> 00:47:15,752
反正你也会成为国王的奴隶
You will end up as his slave
like all the others.

602
00:47:15,836 --> 00:47:16,920
我…
I...

603
00:47:43,238 --> 00:47:45,616
来了，请等一下
Yes, yes. Just a moment.

604
00:47:53,749 --> 00:47:55,042
国王？
The king?

605
00:47:55,459 --> 00:47:57,377
在这个时候
At this hour of the night?

606
00:47:59,338 --> 00:48:03,425
好，那就先等我换件衣服吧
Well, I trust His Majesty won't object
if I put some clothes on first.

607
00:48:13,101 --> 00:48:15,187
你召我来吗，陛下
You sent for me, Your Majesty?

608
00:48:22,152 --> 00:48:23,487
陛下
Your Majesty.

609
00:48:30,619 --> 00:48:33,372
原来陛下在看圣经
Oh, Your Majesty is reading
the Bible.

610
00:48:36,416 --> 00:48:38,377
安娜夫人
Mrs. Anna,

611
00:48:38,836 --> 00:48:41,338
我觉得摩西这个人实在是笨极了
I think your Moses
shall have been a fool.

612
00:48:42,005 --> 00:48:43,173
摩西？
Moses?

613
00:48:43,423 --> 00:48:46,760
摩西，摩西，摩西
我认为他是个大傻瓜
Moses, Moses, Moses.
I think he shall have been a fool.

614
00:48:46,969 --> 00:48:49,263
他说.
Here it stands written by him

615
00:48:49,346 --> 00:48:52,516
世界是在六天内造成的简直是开玩笑
that the world was created
in six days.

616
00:48:53,183 --> 00:48:54,685
我们都知道…
Now you know and I know

617
00:48:54,768 --> 00:48:57,604
这是经过几百万年演化而成的
that it took many ages
to create world.

618
00:48:58,146 --> 00:49:01,191
他真是个没知识的人才这么写
I think he shall have been a fool
to have written so.

619
00:49:02,025 --> 00:49:03,360
你看呢
What is your opinion?

620
00:49:04,152 --> 00:49:07,739
国王陛下半夜三更的把我叫来，就是为了这件事
Is that why Your Majesty sent for me
at this hour of the night?

621
00:49:07,990 --> 00:49:10,951
没理由，在讲重要事之前，还是先谈摩西
That is not reason, but first
I wish to discuss Moses.

622
00:49:11,034 --> 00:49:13,537
你去哪寻求真实呢
Now, how am I ever to learn truth

623
00:49:13,620 --> 00:49:16,707
如果每本书上写的都不一样的话
if different English books
state different things?

624
00:49:18,625 --> 00:49:23,213
圣经不是一本科学化的书,是由信仰完成的
The Bible was not written by men
of science, but by men of faith.

625
00:49:24,423 --> 00:49:27,009
他们只是在颂扬神创造的奇迹
It was their explanation
of the miracle of creation,

626
00:49:27,176 --> 00:49:31,263
问题不在于几天还是几个世纪造成的
which is the same miracle whether
it took six days or many centuries.

627
00:49:40,272 --> 00:49:42,816
我还是认为摩西是个大笨蛋
I still think your Moses
shall have been a fool.

628
00:49:44,109 --> 00:49:45,736
你高兴怎么认为就怎么认为好了
As you wish, Your Majesty.

629
00:49:45,819 --> 00:49:47,779
请问还有别的事吗
Now, was there something else?

630
00:49:47,863 --> 00:49:49,239
写信
Take letter.

631
00:49:49,990 --> 00:49:52,367
写信？ 现在？
A letter? Now?

632
00:49:52,534 --> 00:49:55,495
现在写，现在的事情现在就做
Now. When else?
Now is always best time.

633
00:49:55,579 --> 00:49:59,416
我要寄给有科学精神的林肯先生
Take letter to Mr. Lincoln of America,
who is very scientific ruler.

634
00:50:01,251 --> 00:50:02,920
好吧，陛下
Very well, Your Majesty.

635
00:50:03,337 --> 00:50:05,506
"受全宇宙…
<i>From Phra Mama Mongut,</i>

636
00:50:06,423 --> 00:50:09,593
"最高权利祝福的…
by the blessing of the highest
super agency in the world

637
00:50:09,676 --> 00:50:12,679
"泰国国王，君临天下
of the whole universe,
the king of Siam.

638
00:50:13,805 --> 00:50:18,393
"领属至尊，高贵无比，拥有至高无上的权力
Sovereign of all tributary countries
adjacent and in every direction,

639
00:50:18,477 --> 00:50:21,021
等等，等等"
et cetera, et cetera, et cetera.

640
00:50:22,773 --> 00:50:25,442
你不尊敬国王吗
Do you not have any respect for me?

641
00:50:27,152 --> 00:50:28,654
为什么你站着比我的头还高呢
Why do you stand over my head?

642
00:50:29,112 --> 00:50:31,281
任何时间都不许站在我面前
I cannot stand all the time.

643
00:50:31,782 --> 00:50:35,118
在这个国家，是不允许低头看国王的
And in this country no one's head
shall be higher than king's.

644
00:50:36,453 --> 00:50:39,623
你必须像我其他的臣下一样…
From now on in presence, you shall
so conduct like all other subjects.

645
00:50:40,791 --> 00:50:42,292
你是要我趴在地上
You mean, on the floor?

646
00:50:42,584 --> 00:50:44,461
所有的人都是这么做的
All subjects do so.

647
00:50:45,045 --> 00:50:46,505
非常抱歉，陛下
I'm very sorry.

648
00:50:46,588 --> 00:50:50,217
我最多只能把头低下
I shall try my best not to let my head
be higher than Your Majesty's,

649
00:50:50,676 --> 00:50:53,053
可我拒绝趴在地上
but I simply cannot
grovel on the floor.

650
00:50:53,136 --> 00:50:56,139
因为那样我就无法写信了
I couldn't possibly
work that way, or think.

651
00:51:02,855 --> 00:51:05,816
你是个顽固的女人.
You are very difficult woman!

652
00:51:05,899 --> 00:51:07,860
也许如此，陛下
Perhaps so, Your Majesty.

653
00:51:07,943 --> 00:51:10,571
总之我不许你低头看我
But observe care that head
shall not be higher than mine.

654
00:51:10,654 --> 00:51:14,366
我坐下时你也得坐下，我跪下时你也得跪下…
When I shall sit, you shall sit!
When I shall kneel, you shall kneel.

655
00:51:14,449 --> 00:51:17,160
等等，等等
Et cetera, et cetera, et cetera!

656
00:51:19,329 --> 00:51:21,206
遵命，陛下
Very well, Your Majesty.

657
00:51:22,541 --> 00:51:24,251
这算是承诺吗
Is promise?

658
00:51:27,629 --> 00:51:30,507
是承诺
很好
- Is promise.
- Good.

659
00:51:38,557 --> 00:51:42,477
"美利坚合众国的…
To His Royal Presidency
of the United States in America...

660
00:51:42,561 --> 00:51:44,771
"亚伯拉罕，林肯先生…"
"Abrahom Lingkong"...

661
00:51:46,940 --> 00:51:48,817
写个适当的称呼
...et cetera. You fix up.

662
00:51:50,360 --> 00:51:52,529
"非常突然的…"
It has occurred to us...

663
00:51:54,323 --> 00:51:57,659
"就是非常突然的…"
You see, it has occurred to us...

664
00:52:09,129 --> 00:52:12,549
"非常突然的，让我送几头
It has occurred to us that if we
shall be sending you several pairs

665
00:52:12,633 --> 00:52:14,843
"公象给你们吧…
of young male elephants

666
00:52:15,135 --> 00:52:18,555
只要放到美国的大森林里
to be turned loose
in forests of America...

667
00:52:19,181 --> 00:52:20,933
美国
A-mer-i-ca.

668
00:52:22,142 --> 00:52:24,186
"我想.
We are of opinion

669
00:52:24,269 --> 00:52:27,898
"总有一天，大象的数量是会增多的
that after a while
they shall increase in number.

670
00:52:28,524 --> 00:52:31,527
会越来越多'
陛下…
- And inhabitants of America shall...
- Your Majesty.

671
00:52:31,610 --> 00:52:32,653
什么事
Well?

672
00:52:32,736 --> 00:52:35,864
你不是说只送公象吗
I don't think you mean pairs
of male elephants.

673
00:52:35,948 --> 00:52:38,075
你不要插嘴行吗？
How can I make letter if you interrupt?

674
00:52:38,575 --> 00:52:43,163
"这样一来.就可以加紧驯服.
And inhabitants of America shall be
able to catch and tame them

675
00:52:43,247 --> 00:52:46,500
利用他们搬运货物"
and use them as beasts of burden.

676
00:52:46,583 --> 00:52:49,461
只有公象吗，陛下？
Only male elephants, Your Majesty?

677
00:52:54,341 --> 00:52:56,134
你可以写的更加详细点
You put in the details.

678
00:52:56,218 --> 00:52:57,594
晚安
Good night.

679
00:53:03,559 --> 00:53:04,726
摩西
Moses.

680
00:53:05,227 --> 00:53:06,270
林肯
Lincoln!

681
00:53:06,353 --> 00:53:07,646
大象
Elephants!

682
00:53:07,729 --> 00:53:10,649
半夜叫我趴在地上
Groveling on the floor
at 2:00 in the morning.

683
00:53:12,109 --> 00:53:13,110
夫人，我是伦塔
I am Lun Tha.

684
00:53:13,777 --> 00:53:15,821
你是家庭教师安娜夫人吗
You are Mrs. Anna, schoolteacher?

685
00:53:15,988 --> 00:53:18,115
是的，可这禁止男人进入
Yes, but you shouldn't be...

686
00:53:18,365 --> 00:53:21,243
我非常想见达布提求求你了
I must meet with Tuptim again.
Please!

687
00:53:21,785 --> 00:53:23,745
你们以前在这见过面？
You have been seeing her here?

688
00:53:24,371 --> 00:53:25,747
见过两次
Twice we have spoken.

689
00:53:25,831 --> 00:53:28,125
但戒备森严
Each time it becomes more difficult.

690
00:53:28,333 --> 00:53:30,210
她说过，你可以帮我们
She has said you will help us.

691
00:53:30,919 --> 00:53:32,546
不，不行
Oh, no, I couldn't!

692
00:53:32,629 --> 00:53:34,173
那样做太危险了
It's much too dangerous.

693
00:53:34,256 --> 00:53:36,508
我很为你们的安全担心
Not for me, but for Tuptim and you.

694
00:53:36,592 --> 00:53:40,929
在男人的禁地如被发现就活不了了，马上离开
You'll be killed if they find you in
the City of Women. You must leave!

695
00:53:41,346 --> 00:53:45,392
与其痛苦的活着,还不如死了算了
求你了，安娜夫人
Death is not worse pain than
empty life. Please, Mrs. Anna.

696
00:53:46,351 --> 00:53:48,103
抱歉
I'm sorry, Lun Tha.

697
00:53:48,187 --> 00:53:50,189
我不能帮你的忙
There's nothing I can do.

698
00:54:09,499 --> 00:54:10,959
你等着
Wait there.

699
00:55:14,189 --> 00:55:15,399
达布提
Tuptim.

700
00:55:16,066 --> 00:55:17,818
伦塔
Oh, Lun Tha.

701
00:55:17,901 --> 00:55:20,320
我已经无法再忍耐
Seeing you this way is not enough.

702
00:55:22,072 --> 00:55:24,157
但是我们又能怎么样呢
There is nothing we can do.

703
00:55:25,909 --> 00:55:29,037
随时都有人监视着我
I am watched too closely.

704
00:55:30,706 --> 00:55:34,084
难道我们要永远这样下去吗
Must we go on forever
hiding our love like this?

705
00:55:37,087 --> 00:55:42,009
在黑暗中拥吻
<i>We kiss in a shadow</i>

706
00:55:42,092 --> 00:55:47,055
避开明亮的月光
<i>We hide from the moon,</i>

707
00:55:47,139 --> 00:55:49,933
相逢之期渺茫
<i>Our meetings are few</i>

708
00:55:50,017 --> 00:55:55,063
时光飞逝
<i>and over too soon.</i>

709
00:55:57,107 --> 00:56:01,945
我们耳语
<i>We speak in a whisper,</i>

710
00:56:02,029 --> 00:56:05,949
害怕被偷听
<i>Afraid to be heard;</i>

711
00:56:07,117 --> 00:56:09,870
害怕见到人影
<i>When people are near,</i>

712
00:56:09,953 --> 00:56:14,583
不敢说话
<i>We speak not a word.</i>

713
00:56:17,044 --> 00:56:21,757
一些其他的事情
<i>Alone in our secret,</i>

714
00:56:21,840 --> 00:56:25,552
保守着我们的秘密
<i>Together we sigh</i>

715
00:56:25,636 --> 00:56:29,515
等待
<i>for one smiling day</i>

716
00:56:29,598 --> 00:56:35,646
我们相逢的那天
<i>to be free,</i>

717
00:56:37,314 --> 00:56:42,027
为了在阳光下亲吻
<i>To kiss in the sunlight,</i>

718
00:56:42,611 --> 00:56:46,990
以响彻云霄的声音呐喊
<i>And say to the sky:</i>

719
00:56:47,741 --> 00:56:50,244
"相信我们的爱"
<i>Behold and believe</i>

720
00:56:50,327 --> 00:56:56,333
永远相信
<i>what you see!</i>

721
00:56:56,834 --> 00:56:59,378
'爱我"
<i>Behold</i>

722
00:56:59,461 --> 00:57:04,007
我爱的人
<i>how my lover</i>

723
00:57:04,967 --> 00:57:10,722
爱我
<i>loves me!</i>

724
00:57:14,518 --> 00:57:16,645
什么时候我们才能成为那样呢？
When will we be together, Tuptim?

725
00:57:16,728 --> 00:57:17,855
什么时候？
When?

726
00:57:18,355 --> 00:57:20,148
恐怕永远都无法实现…
It can never be, Lun Tha.

727
00:57:20,983 --> 00:57:22,192
永远不会
Not ever.

728
00:57:24,987 --> 00:57:30,075
在阳光下拥吻
<i>To kiss in the sunlight</i>

729
00:57:30,158 --> 00:57:35,122
以响彻云霄的声音呐喊
<i>And say to the sky:</i>

730
00:57:35,205 --> 00:57:37,958
"相信我们的爱"
<i>Behold and believe</i>

731
00:57:38,041 --> 00:57:43,005
永远相信
<i>What you see!</i>

732
00:57:44,506 --> 00:57:47,134
爱我
<i>Behold</i>

733
00:57:47,217 --> 00:57:53,390
我爱的人
<i>how my lover</i>

734
00:57:53,473 --> 00:57:59,980
"爱我"
<i>loves me!</i>

735
00:58:10,574 --> 00:58:12,576
你得走了
You must go now.

736
00:58:12,659 --> 00:58:15,913
我再不回去就要被发现，那就麻烦了
I will be missed, and they will
start searching for me.

737
00:58:20,250 --> 00:58:22,753
总有一天我要带你离开这的
When I return, it will be
to take you from here.

738
00:58:24,338 --> 00:58:25,881
那是不可能的
There is no way, Lun Tha.

739
00:58:26,089 --> 00:58:28,550
我们从河上逃走
There is a river. There are boats.

740
00:58:28,634 --> 00:58:30,010
我会寻找路线的
I will find a way.

741
00:58:30,928 --> 00:58:32,596
如果可能的话
Oh, if it could only be.

742
00:58:32,930 --> 00:58:35,599
绝对有可能
It will be. I swear this.

743
00:58:35,933 --> 00:58:38,435
等我安排好了，就来通知你
When all is arranged,I will get word to you.

744
00:58:40,562 --> 00:58:42,064
我为你祈祷
I shall pray, Lun Tha.

745
00:58:50,989 --> 00:58:53,992
当你再看到这种花落的时候
If you see a chaba flower in your
path, broken like this,

746
00:58:54,076 --> 00:58:57,329
就是我来接你的信号，记住
it will be the sign that
I have come for you. Watch for it.

747
00:58:58,163 --> 00:58:59,790
我会准备好等着你
I will be ready.

748
00:59:31,822 --> 00:59:33,407
停下，停下，停下
Stop, stop, STUD!

749
00:59:34,950 --> 00:59:36,994
陛下
什么事
- Your Majesty.
- What, what, what?

750
00:59:39,329 --> 00:59:40,455
什么事
Well?

751
00:59:40,789 --> 00:59:43,625
去年割让领土给法国
When Siam's richest province
was stolen by France,

752
00:59:43,709 --> 00:59:46,795
我有不安的预感
I warned it was only
beginning of Western treachery.

753
00:59:48,755 --> 00:59:51,258
再这样下去
If enemies of ours,
with lies such as this

754
00:59:51,341 --> 00:59:54,595
英国也会象这样侵占我们的领土了
can convince British that you are
unfit to be ruler of Siam,

755
00:59:54,678 --> 00:59:58,599
我国将会成为侵略者的食饵
our seas will soon be thick
with ships, greedy for conquest.

756
01:00:01,268 --> 01:00:03,270
如果真是那样
So it has finally come.

757
01:00:04,688 --> 01:00:06,315
后果将不堪设想
We must act quickly.

758
01:00:07,232 --> 01:00:08,859
可我们应该怎么办
But how? Where?

759
01:00:09,776 --> 01:00:11,153
这时我应该
I must think.

760
01:00:11,236 --> 01:00:13,405
冷静的和科学性的思考
Clearly. Scientifically.

761
01:00:14,072 --> 01:00:15,365
我必须思考
I must think.

762
01:00:16,783 --> 01:00:20,370
可他们这样，我无法思考
But how can I think
while being driven out of mind!

763
01:00:22,915 --> 01:00:27,586
灿烂的阳光
<i>A charm from the skies</i>

764
01:00:27,669 --> 01:00:33,133
慈祥的抚慰着我们
<i>Seems to hallow us there</i>

765
01:00:33,467 --> 01:00:37,930
无论我们在哪
<i>Which seek through the world,</i>

766
01:00:38,055 --> 01:00:45,062
都会照射我们
<i>ls ne'er met with elsewhere.</i>

767
01:00:46,313 --> 01:00:48,941
真是好极了，可以打满分
That was splendid. Very effective.

768
01:00:50,734 --> 01:00:51,902
现在…
Now...

769
01:00:54,071 --> 01:00:56,990
早安，陛下
你教这样的课
- Good morning.
- You think you teach king lesson!

770
01:00:57,074 --> 01:01:00,285
我无法付你高薪
This is one lesson you do not
be paid for teaching!

771
01:01:00,369 --> 01:01:05,999
我不允许你教我的孩子甜蜜的家这类的书
You will stop instructing wives
and children in"Home <i>Sweet</i> House"

772
01:01:06,083 --> 01:01:09,878
你总是在提醒我，没有兑现承诺，等等
in order to remind me of breaking
promises I never make, et cetera.

773
01:01:09,962 --> 01:01:14,508
陛下.我在这无法养育我的儿子
Your Majesty, I do not intend to have
my boy brought up in a harem.

774
01:01:14,591 --> 01:01:18,345
你答应过在皇宫旁边给我建一座房子
You did promise me a house.
"A brick residence adjoining the palace."

775
01:01:18,428 --> 01:01:22,766
你在信中答应过的
我不记得有过这种事
- Those were your very words.
- I do not remember such words!

776
01:01:23,141 --> 01:01:25,435
我还记得
我记得
- I remember them.
- I will do remembering!

777
01:01:26,270 --> 01:01:27,771
在这谁是国王
Who is king here?

778
01:01:28,272 --> 01:01:32,192
我提醒你,我要你记住
我不记得什么承诺
I remind you so you remember that.
I do not remember any promises.

779
01:01:32,276 --> 01:01:35,946
我不记得任何事,因为你是我的仆人
I do not remember anything
except that you are my servant.

780
01:01:37,197 --> 01:01:39,241
不，陛下
Oh, no, Your Majesty.

781
01:01:39,741 --> 01:01:40,826
什么
What, what, what?

782
01:01:42,077 --> 01:01:43,954
记住，你只是我的仆人而已
I said, you are my servant!

783
01:01:44,121 --> 01:01:48,292
不，陛下，不是，我不是你的仆人
No, Your Majesty, that is not true.
I am most certainly not your servant!

784
01:01:48,458 --> 01:01:51,170
如果你不照约定给我房子的话…
If you do not give me
the house you promised,

785
01:01:51,253 --> 01:01:53,380
我就立刻回英国去
I shall be forced
to return to England.

786
01:01:53,839 --> 01:01:55,924
不，不，安娜夫人
No! No! Please, Mrs. Anna.

787
01:01:56,300 --> 01:01:58,468
我们相信老师
Please. We believe schoolteacher!

788
01:01:58,552 --> 01:02:00,304
我们相信有雪
I believe in snow!

789
01:02:00,637 --> 01:02:02,097
请挽留她
Do not let her go away.

790
01:02:02,181 --> 01:02:04,933
我绝对不允许有人反抗我
I let her do nothing
that is not my pleasure.

791
01:02:05,017 --> 01:02:07,978
你必须留在这…
It is my pleasure that you stay here!

792
01:02:08,061 --> 01:02:11,398
必须留在皇宫里不许；离开
In palace! In palace!

793
01:02:11,481 --> 01:02:13,150
不，陛下
No, Your Majesty.

794
01:02:15,402 --> 01:02:18,030
你怎么忍心丢下这些孩子不管呢
Why do you wish
to leave these children,

795
01:02:18,113 --> 01:02:21,575
他们是多么的喜欢你，女教师
all of whom are loving you
so extraordinarily?

796
01:02:21,658 --> 01:02:26,371
我当然不希望离开他们，我也很喜欢他们
I do not wish to leave them. I love
them too, quite extraordinarily.

797
01:02:26,747 --> 01:02:29,708
可我无法留在一个不守信用的国家
I cannot stay where a promise
has no meaning.

798
01:02:29,791 --> 01:02:30,918
请你说话放尊重点…
I will hear no more!

799
01:02:31,001 --> 01:02:33,754
你说想要把泰国发展成为
A land where there is a wish
for Siam

800
01:02:33,837 --> 01:02:36,173
一个现代的国家
to take her place
in the modern world,

801
01:02:36,256 --> 01:02:40,844
你只是嘴上说说而已，实际上还是保持着旧态
but where everything still remains
according to the wishes of the king!

802
01:02:40,928 --> 01:02:43,055
你应该听我的
You will say no more! No more!

803
01:02:43,138 --> 01:02:46,558
我不会再说什么了，该说的我都说了
I will say no more, because
there is no more to say!

804
01:02:46,892 --> 01:02:47,893
我们走，路易
Come, Louis.

805
01:02:50,062 --> 01:02:51,647
退下
Out, out, out!

806
01:03:20,551 --> 01:03:21,760
是谁
Who is it?

807
01:03:21,844 --> 01:03:24,346
是我，张妃
Mrs. Anna, it is I, Lady Thiang.

808
01:03:25,055 --> 01:03:27,432
请进来，张妃
Oh, well, come in, Lady Thiang.

809
01:03:31,019 --> 01:03:34,815
安娜夫人，请立刻去向国王报道
Mrs. Anna, you must
go to king at once.

810
01:03:34,898 --> 01:03:37,276
为什么要那样做呢？
Indeed? And why must I?

811
01:03:37,359 --> 01:03:40,070
我的任务已经完成了,打算坐下班船回英国
I plan to leave on the next sailing.

812
01:03:40,153 --> 01:03:41,822
求求你了，安娜夫人
Please, Mrs. Anna.

813
01:03:42,239 --> 01:03:44,491
是他派你来说服我的
Did he send you here to ask me?

814
01:03:44,575 --> 01:03:46,994
不，是我自己来的
No. It is I who ask you.

815
01:03:47,744 --> 01:03:50,873
国王现在正面临困境
King is in terrible distress,
not knowing where to turn.

816
01:03:50,956 --> 01:03:52,249
困境
Distress?

817
01:03:52,624 --> 01:03:58,005
他得到一封新加坡寄给英国政府的信
Agents in Singapore have found copies
of letters to British government

818
01:03:58,088 --> 01:04:01,133
说泰国国王是野蛮人…
which describe king as barbarian

819
01:04:01,216 --> 01:04:05,846
应该归英国管才对
and suggest necessity
of making Siam a protectorate.

820
01:04:05,929 --> 01:04:08,557
哦，怎么能那样
Oh, but that is outrageous!

821
01:04:08,640 --> 01:04:12,895
虽然国王有很多缺点,可他并不是野蛮人
The king is many things I dislike,
but he is not a barbarian.

822
01:04:12,978 --> 01:04:14,771
你答应帮他了？
Then you will go to him now?

823
01:04:14,855 --> 01:04:17,357
你是要我提供意见给他
You mean, to advise him?

824
01:04:18,192 --> 01:04:20,944
不是建议
It must not sound like advice.

825
01:04:21,028 --> 01:04:23,739
国王不需要任何意见
King cannot take advice.

826
01:04:23,822 --> 01:04:28,285
你自己向他提出这件事
And he will not bring up subject.
You must do it for him.

827
01:04:30,704 --> 01:04:34,791
不行，张妃,我也有自己的立场
No, Lady Thiang, I can't.
It's against all my principles.

828
01:04:35,751 --> 01:04:38,128
他需要帮助，安娜夫人
He needs help, Mrs. Anna.

829
01:04:38,295 --> 01:04:40,130
你可以帮他
Oh, but he has you.

830
01:04:40,547 --> 01:04:43,967
我无法胜任这个重任
I am not equal to his special needs.

831
01:04:46,428 --> 01:04:51,391
不行，张妃
Please, Lady Thiang, I simply cannot
go to him, especially without

832
01:04:51,475 --> 01:04:52,851
何况他本人没有求我
his having asked for me.

833
01:04:54,144 --> 01:04:56,313
你还要我说什么呢？
What more can I say to you?

834
01:04:57,814 --> 01:05:02,569
他是个很用心思考的人
<i>This is a man
who thinks with his heart,</i>

835
01:05:02,653 --> 01:05:07,824
虽然有时欠缺思考
<i>His heart is not always wise.</i>

836
01:05:08,617 --> 01:05:12,913
即使绊倒了
<i>This is a man who stumbles and falls.</i>

837
01:05:12,996 --> 01:05:18,418
也会再试的
<i>But this is a man who tries.</i>

838
01:05:19,503 --> 01:05:24,591
请原谅他的过错
<i>This is a man you'll forgive and forgive,</i>

839
01:05:24,675 --> 01:05:28,095
帮帮他
<i>and help and protect,</i>

840
01:05:28,178 --> 01:05:35,185
只要你活着
<i>as long as you live.</i>

841
01:05:45,070 --> 01:05:50,534
他就不会说
<i>He will not always say</i>

842
01:05:50,617 --> 01:05:55,706
即使他没有遵守承诺
<i>What you would have him say,</i>

843
01:05:56,373 --> 01:06:00,627
可他会说些别的
<i>But now and then he'll say</i>

844
01:06:00,711 --> 01:06:06,717
来讨你的欢心
<i>something wonderful.</i>

845
01:06:07,885 --> 01:06:13,307
让你忘掉不快
<i>The thoughtless things he'll do</i>

846
01:06:13,390 --> 01:06:18,437
忘掉对你的伤害
<i>will hurt and worry you.</i>

847
01:06:19,354 --> 01:06:23,775
他会做的很好
<i>Then all at once he'll do</i>

848
01:06:23,859 --> 01:06:29,281
他有几千个
<i>something wonderful.</i>

849
01:06:29,865 --> 01:06:34,578
无法实现的梦
<i>He has a thousand dreams</i>

850
01:06:34,661 --> 01:06:38,957
你知道
<i>that won't come true,</i>

851
01:06:39,249 --> 01:06:44,588
他很相信他们
<i>You know that he believes in them,</i>

852
01:06:44,671 --> 01:06:47,841
那样对你够了
<i>And that's enough</i>

853
01:06:47,925 --> 01:06:52,888
如果他错了
<i>for you</i>

854
01:06:53,972 --> 01:06:59,436
有你在他身后
<i>You'll always go along,</i>

855
01:07:00,020 --> 01:07:04,816
告诉他错了
<i>Defend him when he's wrong,</i>

856
01:07:05,943 --> 01:07:09,780
当需要时提醒他
<i>And tell him when he's strong,</i>

857
01:07:10,280 --> 01:07:16,328
他会很出色的
<i>He is wonderful.</i>

858
01:07:16,411 --> 01:07:22,709
他一直需要你的爱
<i>He'll always need your love,</i>

859
01:07:23,460 --> 01:07:30,259
他要得到你的爱
<i>And so he'll get your love.</i>

860
01:07:31,802 --> 01:07:38,141
一个需要你爱的男人
<i>A man who needs your love</i>

861
01:07:39,268 --> 01:07:42,604
会的
<i>can be</i>

862
01:07:42,688 --> 01:07:49,319
会很出色
<i>wonderful.</i>

863
01:08:21,935 --> 01:08:23,353
陛下
Your Majesty.

864
01:08:23,729 --> 01:08:25,439
你是来道歉的
You have come to apologize.

865
01:08:25,522 --> 01:08:28,483
对不起，陛下--
这样就足够了
- I am sorry, Your Majesty, but...
- Good! You apologize.

866
01:08:28,567 --> 01:08:30,652
我并没有说-
我原谅你了
- I didn't say...
- I accept.

867
01:08:32,571 --> 01:08:34,406
谢谢你.陛下
Thank you, Your Majesty.

868
01:08:36,909 --> 01:08:38,035
是吗？
Well?

869
01:08:38,702 --> 01:08:40,746
如你所见，我正在想一些事情
Do you not see I am occupied?

870
01:08:41,330 --> 01:08:44,082
考虑一些重要的问题
My mind on very important matters.

871
01:08:47,085 --> 01:08:49,713
有什么事情愿意告诉我吗？
Anything you wish to discuss with me?

872
01:08:54,218 --> 01:08:57,054
我是不会对女人谈政治的？
Why should I discuss important matter with woman?

873
01:08:57,137 --> 01:09:00,682
很好，陛下，那么晚安了
Very well, Your Majesty. In that case
I shall say good night.

874
01:09:01,225 --> 01:09:02,601
晚安！
Good night!

875
01:09:12,069 --> 01:09:13,695
陛下
Your Majesty...

876
01:09:13,904 --> 01:09:15,489
什么事？什么事？什么事？
我很好奇
- What, what, what?
- I wonder...

877
01:09:15,864 --> 01:09:18,450
今天有艘船从新加坡来--
新加坡，是的
- When the boat came from Singapore...
- Singapore!

878
01:09:18,534 --> 01:09:21,411
带来什么消息吗？
消息！
- Was there any news from abroad?
- News!

879
01:09:21,787 --> 01:09:23,163
当然有了
There were news!

880
01:09:23,539 --> 01:09:26,625
他们居然说我是野蛮人！
谁？
- They call me barbarian.
- Who?

881
01:09:26,708 --> 01:09:29,878
他们正想利用这个籍口来侵略我们
Parties who would use this
as excuse to steal my country.

882
01:09:29,962 --> 01:09:32,339
如果你是英国女王的话…
Now suppose
you are Queen Victoria,

883
01:09:32,422 --> 01:09:36,176
有人说泰国是个野蛮的国家，你会信么？
and someone say to you king of Siam
is barbarian. Do you believe?

884
01:09:36,260 --> 01:09:38,428
陛下--
你会
- Well, Your Majesty...
- You will!

885
01:09:38,512 --> 01:09:43,141
如果所有的人都是这么说的话
You will believe I am because
there is no one to speak otherwise.

886
01:09:43,225 --> 01:09:45,060
但这是个谎言
Oh, but this is a lie!

887
01:09:45,143 --> 01:09:47,437
这是个天大的谎言！
It is a false lie!

888
01:09:56,363 --> 01:09:58,907
陛下，你打算怎么办？
What have you decided
to do about it?

889
01:10:07,332 --> 01:10:09,501
你猜猜看
You guess.

890
01:10:13,755 --> 01:10:14,965
好吧
Well,

891
01:10:15,174 --> 01:10:18,385
如果有人在英王面前讲了我的谎话
if someone were sending a lie
about me to England,

892
01:10:18,468 --> 01:10:21,430
我会努力的将事情的真相传到英国
I would do my best to send
the truth to England.

893
01:10:21,513 --> 01:10:24,308
陛下，你也会这么做吧？
Is that what you have decided to do,
Your Majesty?

894
01:10:24,391 --> 01:10:27,477
是的，我是这么打算的，但是怎么做呢？
Yes, that is what I have
decided to do. But how?

895
01:10:28,937 --> 01:10:31,440
但是你猜猜我现在会怎么做呢
Guess how I shall do this.

896
01:10:32,274 --> 01:10:35,319
我一定是想办法
Well, my guess would be
that you would seek

897
01:10:35,402 --> 01:10:38,238
与英国去亲近
some kind of personal contact
with the British.

898
01:10:38,322 --> 01:10:42,242
对了！正好可以利用在这儿访问的大使
Personal contact! When British
ambassador and party arrive in Siam...

899
01:10:42,326 --> 01:10:43,952
英国大使要到这儿吗？
The ambassador, here?

900
01:10:44,203 --> 01:10:47,247
我想他会来的
他们正在做东洋的亲善访问
On quick tour of Orient.
Friendship tour, they say.

901
01:10:47,414 --> 01:10:51,502
莱杰大臣已来报告过了，那么说爱德华也会来？
I receive letters from his aide, Sir
Edward Ramsay, who accompanies him.

902
01:10:51,835 --> 01:10:53,837
爱德华要来？
Edward, coming here?

903
01:10:56,340 --> 01:10:57,633
爱德华？
"Edward"?

904
01:10:59,176 --> 01:11:00,469
你这样称呼他？
You call him this?

905
01:11:01,094 --> 01:11:05,224
我和爱德华是老朋友了，结婚前就认识
We are old friends. I knew him
in London before I was married.

906
01:11:10,562 --> 01:11:14,358
我会对那些侵略者表示出一些想法
When they're here, I'll take
opportunity of expressing my opinion

907
01:11:14,441 --> 01:11:17,152
我要让他们知道
of thieves who would try
to steal my country.

908
01:11:17,236 --> 01:11:20,614
到底谁是野蛮人，野蛮人
I will show them who is barbarian!

909
01:11:23,659 --> 01:11:25,786
你的脸是怎么了？
Well, what is this face you put on?

910
01:11:25,869 --> 01:11:30,832
你是不会和来宾发生冲突的吧
My guess is that you will not fight
with your distinguished visitors.

911
01:11:30,916 --> 01:11:33,126
我当然不会？
是的，陛下
- I will not?
- No, Your Majesty.

912
01:11:33,502 --> 01:11:36,505
我想你会举行一个盛大的宴会
You will give a banquet
in their honor.

913
01:11:36,755 --> 01:11:39,967
非常热情地款待每个人让他们玩得尽兴
You will entertain them in
a particularly grand manner.

914
01:11:40,050 --> 01:11:43,011
这样的话,他们就会知道你是个热心的人
You will make them all
witnesses in your favor.

915
01:11:43,095 --> 01:11:45,472
他们回到英国一定会向女王作善意的报告
They will return to England
and report to the queen

916
01:11:45,556 --> 01:11:48,559
你的善意会证明你不是一个野蛮人
that you are most certainly
not a barbarian.

917
01:11:51,061 --> 01:11:52,646
对！
Naturally!

918
01:11:55,941 --> 01:11:58,944
太对了！当然我就是打算那么做的
Naturally! This is what
I shall have intended to do.

919
01:12:00,070 --> 01:12:02,906
我想，陛下，这个时候
That's it, Your Majesty.
Stand up to them.

920
01:12:02,990 --> 01:12:05,075
你得把自己最好的一面表现出来
Put your best foot forward.

921
01:12:07,536 --> 01:12:09,705
不是表情，陛下
It's an expression, Your Majesty.

922
01:12:09,788 --> 01:12:12,207
我的意思是你最好穿上最华丽的衣服
It means put on your best clothes,

923
01:12:12,291 --> 01:12:16,003
招一些智者和美女出席
show them your most intelligent men
and most beautiful women.

924
01:12:16,086 --> 01:12:20,841
但美女们如果光着脚那又会怎么样呢？
Shall it be proper for the British
to see my women without shoes?

925
01:12:20,924 --> 01:12:24,845
想要加把劲改善一下也不是不可能的吧？
Shall it be proper for my women
to put their best bare feet forward?

926
01:12:25,596 --> 01:12:28,765
不！我想让她们学西方贵族
No, we shall make them look
like ladies of Europe:

927
01:12:28,849 --> 01:12:30,559
在脚上穿上漂亮的鞋子
Shoes on feet, dresses on bodies.

928
01:12:30,642 --> 01:12:33,687
由你来选择这些女孩子穿上洋装
You will tell me which ladies
are most like Europeans

929
01:12:33,770 --> 01:12:37,316
由你来教她们西方的习惯以及礼节
and educate them in European
customs and manner for presentation.

930
01:12:37,399 --> 01:12:39,693
当然，衣物也由你缝制
我缝制？
- Also, sew dresses.
- Sew dresses?

931
01:12:39,776 --> 01:12:41,153
是的，女孩子们会帮你的
All women shall help.

932
01:12:41,236 --> 01:12:44,031
不，陛下…我想就以贵国的
Don't you think it would
make a better impression

933
01:12:44,114 --> 01:12:46,700
服装和礼仪来迎接…
in their own manner and dress?

934
01:12:46,783 --> 01:12:51,121
你说怎么样呀？我们是泰国人，一眼就看得明白
You are not being scientific.
The ambassador knows we are Siamese.

935
01:12:51,205 --> 01:12:53,665
但是想让他们看看我们也接受西方文明
I wish him to know
we are also Europeans.

936
01:12:53,749 --> 01:12:55,709
醒醒！大家到寺庙里集合，快起床吧！
Wake up! Everybody to the temple!

937
01:12:57,294 --> 01:13:00,797
醒醒！妃子，王子，等等，等等！
Wake up, wake up, wives,
et cetera, et cetera, et cetera.

938
01:13:00,881 --> 01:13:03,217
对了，我们还可以表演戏剧、杂技什么的！
We will entertain them with acrobats.

939
01:13:03,300 --> 01:13:06,345
就表演戏剧
We could give them
a theatrical performance.

940
01:13:06,428 --> 01:13:10,849
达布堤改编的"汤姆叔叔的小屋."
Tuptim has written a play, her own
version of Uncle Tom's <i>Cabin.</i>

941
01:13:10,933 --> 01:13:14,645
我们就表演戏剧，让他们知道谁才是野蛮人
We shall give them theatricals.
We'll show them who is barbarian.

942
01:13:14,728 --> 01:13:17,481
晚餐的餐具也是西式的
We could make European dishes
for dinner.

943
01:13:17,564 --> 01:13:21,693
对的，要教他们坐椅子和高脚桌子
You teach. To be served
on high table. Long white tablecloth...

944
01:13:21,777 --> 01:13:23,862
桌面上还要铺白桌布
还有餐巾，用最好的丝绸
- And napkins.
- Of finest silk.

945
01:13:23,946 --> 01:13:26,740
用最好的黄金筷子
筷子？
- Using best gold chopsticks.
- Chopsticks?

946
01:13:26,823 --> 01:13:30,160
不认为刀叉会更合适吗，陛下？
Don't you think knives and forks
would be more suitable?

947
01:13:30,244 --> 01:13:34,206
其实英国的刀叉不如筷子科学
British not scientific enough
for the use of chopsticks.

948
01:13:34,289 --> 01:13:37,626
那么就订制一些金制的刀叉
You are to order finest
gold knives and forks.

949
01:13:37,709 --> 01:13:42,297
还有汤勺
你怎么会忘记汤勺呢？
Also spoons.
Why do you not think of spoons?

950
01:13:42,381 --> 01:13:45,384
陛下，你可真细心
An inspired idea, Your Majesty.

951
01:13:45,467 --> 01:13:48,637
噢，对了，还有雪茄
英国人很喜欢雪茄的
We mustn't forget cigars.
Englishmen are fond of them.

952
01:13:48,720 --> 01:13:52,599
路过和在曼谷的西洋人我也会全部邀请
You are to make list of all eminent
Europeans residing in Bangkok

953
01:13:52,683 --> 01:13:55,352
让他们都来参加宴会
好文章，陛下
- for sending of invitations.
- Very well.

954
01:13:55,435 --> 01:13:59,022
对，你教乐队西方人的舞蹈和…
You will instruct court musicians
their learning music of Europe

955
01:13:59,106 --> 01:14:02,025
音乐怎么样,让他们都学点，等等
for dancing, et cetera,
et cetera, et cetera.

956
01:14:02,109 --> 01:14:03,610
真是好主意，陛下
Excellent, Your Majesty.

957
01:14:03,694 --> 01:14:06,029
那么我有多少时间准备这些？
How much time do I have for all this?

958
01:14:06,113 --> 01:14:09,950
你还有一个星期的时间去准备
British gunboat last reported off
Singkla. This give you one week.

959
01:14:10,033 --> 01:14:13,120
一个星期！陛下，只有一个星期吗？！
One week? Your Majesty, one week!

960
01:14:13,203 --> 01:14:15,289
摩西他曾经说过…
In this same time,

961
01:14:15,372 --> 01:14:19,209
世界是一星期造成的，这可是摩西说的
whole world was created,
Moses say.

962
01:14:27,301 --> 01:14:29,219
来祈求佛祖的保护，下跪吧
First, we ask help from Buddha.

963
01:14:29,303 --> 01:14:31,346
下跪吧！
Bow to him. Bow, bow, bow.

964
01:14:32,639 --> 01:14:33,724
下跪
BOW!

965
01:14:48,697 --> 01:14:53,785
祈祷佛祖，请赐我智慧及力量
Oh, Buddha, give us the aid
of your strength and your wisdom.

966
01:14:54,077 --> 01:14:57,497
祈祷佛祖，请赐我智慧及力量
Oh, Buddha
give us the aid of your strength

967
01:14:57,581 --> 01:15:00,834
祈祷佛祖
and your wisdom.

968
01:15:04,087 --> 01:15:07,049
请赐我智慧及力量向那些英国人证明
And help us to prove
to the visiting English

969
01:15:07,132 --> 01:15:11,220
我们是优秀的民族
that we are extraordinary
and remarkable people.

970
01:15:11,595 --> 01:15:14,973
请帮助我们向那些英国人证明
And help us
to prove to the visiting English

971
01:15:15,057 --> 01:15:19,102
我们是优秀的民族
that we are extraordinary
and remarkable people.

972
01:15:24,107 --> 01:15:29,279
同时也保佑老师昼夜不休尽快将衣服赶制好
Help also Mrs. Anna to keep awake
for scientific sewing of dresses

973
01:15:29,363 --> 01:15:31,698
她虽是个基督教徒
even though she be only
a woman and a Christian,

974
01:15:31,782 --> 01:15:34,952
又是个一无是处的女人…
and therefore unworthy
of your interest.

975
01:15:35,953 --> 01:15:37,871
但请赐给她力量
Help also Mrs. Anna...

976
01:15:37,955 --> 01:15:41,625
陛下，你太过份了--
别忘了，你向我承诺过！
- Your Majesty, this is really--
- A promise is a promise.

977
01:15:41,708 --> 01:15:44,211
你的头不会比我高！
Head must not be higher than mine.

978
01:15:44,795 --> 01:15:46,046
承诺！
A promise!

979
01:15:46,129 --> 01:15:50,592
一无是处
...and therefore
unworthy of your interest.

980
01:15:53,637 --> 01:15:55,681
佛祖
And, Buddha,

981
01:15:55,764 --> 01:15:57,724
当我事成之后我承诺
I promise you

982
01:15:58,809 --> 01:16:01,937
我将为这个女人
that I shall give
this unworthy woman

983
01:16:03,647 --> 01:16:05,107
建一栋房子
a house.

984
01:16:06,775 --> 01:16:09,653
一栋她自己想要的
We will build her a house of her own:

985
01:16:10,988 --> 01:16:12,948
一栋房子
A brick residence

986
01:16:13,490 --> 01:16:16,618
就在皇宫附近
adjoining royal palace

987
01:16:16,702 --> 01:16:18,996
正如契约上所说的
according to agreement,

988
01:16:21,081 --> 01:16:22,624
等等
et cetera,

989
01:16:23,542 --> 01:16:25,085
等等
et cetera,

990
01:16:25,586 --> 01:16:27,379
等等
et cetera.

991
01:16:28,922 --> 01:16:31,550
陛下
- Your Majesty...
- Oh!

992
01:16:31,633 --> 01:16:33,886
为这个一无事外的女人
...this unworthy woman

993
01:16:33,969 --> 01:16:35,304
建一栋房子
a house.

994
01:16:35,387 --> 01:16:38,098
为她建的房子
We will build her
a house of her own.

995
01:16:38,182 --> 01:16:41,476
就在皇宫附近
A brick residence
adjoining royal palace...

996
01:16:41,560 --> 01:16:44,646
正如契约上所说的
...according to agreement...

997
01:16:46,481 --> 01:16:49,234
等等
...et cetera...

998
01:16:50,944 --> 01:16:54,072
等等
...et cetera...

999
01:16:55,657 --> 01:17:00,495
等等
...et cetera.

1000
01:17:44,540 --> 01:17:49,044
餐巾终于送来了，谢天谢地
张妃，请把它们摆列在餐桌上
The napkins finally arrived. Would
you place them on the table please?

1001
01:17:49,127 --> 01:17:51,338
谢谢
不，不必客气
- Thank you.
- No, thank you.

1002
01:17:52,047 --> 01:17:54,508
各位，你们都准备好了吗？
客人们就要来了
Are we ready?
The guests are arriving.

1003
01:17:54,591 --> 01:17:57,177
安娜夫人，会有英国人来吗
Please, do not let
Englishmen come here.

1004
01:17:57,261 --> 01:17:58,554
好可怕呀，安娜夫人
We are afraid.

1005
01:17:58,637 --> 01:18:01,181
他们能用眼睛下咒语
They cast terrible spell
on us with evil eye.

1006
01:18:01,265 --> 01:18:03,475
求求你了，安娜夫人
Oh, nonsense. Nonsense!

1007
01:18:03,559 --> 01:18:05,936
别胡说了,现在，让我来看看
你们准备好了没有
Step back. Let me see how you look.

1008
01:18:07,771 --> 01:18:09,189
分开站着
Stand apart.

1009
01:18:10,440 --> 01:18:13,068
很好,转圈
Very nice. Now, turn round.

1010
01:18:19,032 --> 01:18:21,285
老天！
Oh, my goodness gracious!

1011
01:18:21,535 --> 01:18:22,828
怎么啦？
What is trouble now?

1012
01:18:24,663 --> 01:18:28,750
我忘记了,她们还没内衣
Oh, I forgot! They have practically
no undergarments.

1013
01:18:28,834 --> 01:18:32,546
内衣？有没有穿内衣有什么关系？
Undergarments! Of what importance
are undergarments at this time?

1014
01:18:32,629 --> 01:18:34,339
穿内衣是非常重要的
Of great importance.

1015
01:18:34,423 --> 01:18:36,508
那么你穿了吗？
Are you wearing undergarments?

1016
01:18:36,884 --> 01:18:40,721
所有的英国妇女都会穿内衣的，陛下
All properly dressed English ladies
always wear undergarments.

1017
01:18:40,804 --> 01:18:44,766
照你这么说,英国实在是太落伍了
I have opinion that, in this regard,
England is very backward nation.

1018
01:18:56,612 --> 01:18:58,780
这是你今晚出
席宴会要穿的吗？
Is this what you shall be wearing?

1019
01:18:58,864 --> 01:19:01,283
是的，你喜欢吗？
Why, yes. Do you like it?

1020
01:19:02,659 --> 01:19:03,994
那么…
Well...

1021
01:19:04,411 --> 01:19:08,665
你这样真的没有关系吗？象这些，等等，等等？
Are you certain this is customary,
et cetera, et cetera, et cetera?

1022
01:19:09,875 --> 01:19:13,045
你是说露出胸脯？
What is so extraordinary
about bare shoulders?

1023
01:19:13,128 --> 01:19:14,713
你看，大家都露了--
- Your own ladies...
- Yes.

1024
01:19:14,796 --> 01:19:16,715
但这有些不同…
But is different because
of not wearing

1025
01:19:16,798 --> 01:19:20,552
因为你其它的部位都包得很严严实实
covering-ups on other parts
of body, and therefore...

1026
01:19:20,636 --> 01:19:22,221
比如说这…但只有,那又怎么样呢？
Therefore what?

1027
01:19:23,263 --> 01:19:24,723
不在一样
Is different.

1028
01:19:25,349 --> 01:19:27,226
很抱歉，不能得到你的认同
I'm sorry you do not approve.

1029
01:19:27,309 --> 01:19:28,602
我可没有那么说
I have not said I do not approve.

1030
01:19:31,104 --> 01:19:34,316
陛下，一定是来宾到了
The ambassador and his party
must be arriving.

1031
01:19:34,399 --> 01:19:37,361
安娜夫人，他们是食人族吗
Mrs. Anna, Mrs. Anna.
They are cannibals.

1032
01:19:37,444 --> 01:19:38,946
会被她们吃掉的
They will eat us!

1033
01:19:39,029 --> 01:19:41,365
没那回事
They will do nothing of the kind.

1034
01:19:41,448 --> 01:19:44,785
重要的是,当打招呼时
Remember, when you are
presented to the ambassador,

1035
01:19:44,868 --> 01:19:47,704
切记别让人看见背后的样子
for heaven's sake, keep your backs
to the wall.

1036
01:19:49,665 --> 01:19:50,749
你们明白了吗！
So!

1037
01:19:51,291 --> 01:19:54,962
陛下，他是大英帝国的代表强培大使
Your Majesty, this shall be
His Excellency, Sir John Hay,

1038
01:19:55,045 --> 01:19:59,216
他特意从英国来拜访你
most honorable representative
of United Kingdom in Great Britain.

1039
01:19:59,299 --> 01:20:00,759
国王陛下
Your Majesty.

1040
01:20:01,218 --> 01:20:02,594
欢迎你
I am pleased.

1041
01:20:06,098 --> 01:20:07,558
抽雪茄
Cigar.

1042
01:20:08,141 --> 01:20:09,601
谢谢你，陛下
Thank you, Your Majesty.

1043
01:20:09,685 --> 01:20:12,604
国王陛下，
请容我介绍莱杰副使
May I introduce my aide,
Sir Edward Ramsay.

1044
01:20:12,688 --> 01:20:14,147
国王陛下
Your Majesty.

1045
01:20:14,523 --> 01:20:16,567
你好，抽雪茄
I am pleased. Cigar.

1046
01:20:17,025 --> 01:20:18,193
谢谢你
Thank you.

1047
01:20:18,277 --> 01:20:20,821
啊，她是老师,安娜夫人
And this is Madame Halloweens,

1048
01:20:20,904 --> 01:20:24,491
在皇宫里教英语等等的
teacher of English language,
customs, et cetera, in royal household.

1049
01:20:24,575 --> 01:20:27,119
久闻大名了，夫人
We've heard of
your splendid work here.

1050
01:20:27,202 --> 01:20:29,204
谢谢，大使
Thank you, Your Excellency.

