that this kind of thing can happen,</i>

1395
01:49:38,912 --> 01:49:40,163
我们来跳舞好吗？
<i>Shall we dance?</i>

1396
01:49:40,247 --> 01:49:41,415
我们来跳舞好吗？
<i>Shall we dance?</i>

1397
01:49:41,498 --> 01:49:43,083
我们来跳舞好吗？
<i>Shall we dance?</i>

1398
01:49:56,847 --> 01:49:59,349
你为什么要停下来呢？继续跳啊，跳啊
Why do you stop?
You dance pretty. Go on.

1399
01:49:59,433 --> 01:50:03,270
陛下，我没意识到，再说了，我又不是个舞娘
Your Majesty, I didn't realize.
After all, I'm not a dancing girl.

1400
01:50:03,353 --> 01:50:06,273
在英国，没有女人会
当着一个男人的面独自跳舞
In England, no woman dances alone
while a man looks on.

1401
01:50:06,356 --> 01:50:09,026
但你们和那些不认识的男人跳舞啊
手挽着手，等等
But she dances with stranger,
holding hands?

1402
01:50:09,109 --> 01:50:11,195
是的，但并不经常都是陌生人--
Yes, but not always a stranger.

1403
01:50:11,278 --> 01:50:14,448
也会有我们的好朋友
很好，那我们现在就来跳吧
- Usually a very good friend.
- Then we'll dance together.

1404
01:50:14,531 --> 01:50:16,575
你来教我吧
我来和你跳，怎么样？
You show me.
Teach, teach, teach.

1405
01:50:16,658 --> 01:50:18,410
好的，那是很简单的
It's quite simple, the polka.

1406
01:50:18,493 --> 01:50:21,371
数着1，2，3，就行了.1，2，3
You count, "One, two, three,
and one, two, three...

1407
01:50:21,455 --> 01:50:23,457
1，2，3…
...and one, two, three, and..."

1408
01:50:23,540 --> 01:50:24,708
我们来跳舞吧
<i>Shall we dance?</i>

1409
01:50:24,791 --> 01:50:25,959
1，2，3…
One, two, three, and.

1410
01:50:26,043 --> 01:50:29,338
随着轻快的音乐飞上云霄
<i>On a bright cloud of music shall we fly?</i>

1411
01:50:29,421 --> 01:50:30,631
1，2，3…
One, two, three, and.

1412
01:50:30,714 --> 01:50:31,882
我们来跳舞吧？
<i>Shall we dance?</i>

1413
01:50:31,965 --> 01:50:33,133
1，2，3…
One, two, three, and.

1414
01:50:33,217 --> 01:50:36,345
直跳到晚安说道别前
<i>Shall we then say "goodnight"
and mean "goodbye?"</i>

1415
01:50:36,428 --> 01:50:37,721
1，2，3…
One, two, three, and.

1416
01:50:37,804 --> 01:50:39,264
或许
<i>Oh, perchance</i>

1417
01:50:40,224 --> 01:50:43,936
舞到最后的星星消失时
<i>when the last little star has left the sky.</i>

1418
01:50:44,895 --> 01:50:49,525
我们还是在一起手挽着手
<i>Shall we still be together
with our arms around each other,</i>

1419
01:50:49,608 --> 01:50:53,403
你就会成为我的新恋人
<i>And shall you be my new romance?</i>

1420
01:50:54,321 --> 01:50:58,825
我早就意识到那会发生
<i>On the clear understanding
that this kind of thing can happen,</i>

1421
01:50:58,909 --> 01:51:00,035
我们来跳舞吧？
<i>Shall we dance?</i>

1422
01:51:00,118 --> 01:51:01,328
我们来跳舞吧？
<i>Shall we dance?</i>

1423
01:51:01,411 --> 01:51:02,913
我们来跳舞吧？
<i>Shall we dance?</i>

1424
01:51:03,622 --> 01:51:08,252
现在数1，2，3，
1，2，3--
- And one, two, three--
- One, two, three, one, two, three--

1425
01:51:08,836 --> 01:51:10,212
有点怪怪的
Something wrong.

1426
01:51:10,295 --> 01:51:12,714
我忘了节拍，下次我会记得的
I know, I forgot "and."
Next time I remember.

1427
01:51:12,965 --> 01:51:14,633
1，2，3，
1，2，3
One, two, three,
and one, two, three--

1428
01:51:15,467 --> 01:51:17,344
你跳得很好，陛下
That's splendid, Your Majesty.

1429
01:51:17,427 --> 01:51:19,137
很好，很好
Splendid, splendid!

1430
01:51:20,472 --> 01:51:22,391
你把我的节奏给弄乱了
You throw me off count!

1431
01:51:23,559 --> 01:51:28,063
1，2，3
1，2，3
And, one, two, three, and
one, two, three, and...

1432
01:51:28,897 --> 01:51:30,107
有点不对
That is not right.

1433
01:51:30,190 --> 01:51:32,734
不，这样就对了
就是这样
You were doing beautifully,
Your Majesty.

1434
01:51:32,818 --> 01:51:36,530
这和今晚我看到你跟那个西方人跳的不同
No, no. Not the way I see
Europeans dancing tonight.

1435
01:51:36,780 --> 01:51:39,074
不，就是这样跳的
Yes, it was. It was just like that.

1436
01:51:39,157 --> 01:51:41,785
不是这样的手好像不是这样握的
Were not holding two hands like this.

1437
01:51:47,624 --> 01:51:48,709
这…
No...

1438
01:51:50,377 --> 01:51:52,296
的确不是这样的
...as a matter of fact.

1439
01:51:53,172 --> 01:51:54,339
应该是…
Was...

1440
01:52:01,513 --> 01:52:02,973
这样，不是吗
...like this?

1441
01:52:03,891 --> 01:52:04,933
是吗？
No?

1442
01:52:06,059 --> 01:52:07,227
是的
Yes.

1443
01:52:07,311 --> 01:52:08,437
跳吧
Come.

1444
01:53:05,702 --> 01:53:07,120
来
Come.

1445
01:53:07,204 --> 01:53:08,497
我们再来一次
We do it again.

1446
01:53:22,219 --> 01:53:24,137
陛下
你为什么要来打扰我呢？
- Your Majesty--
- Why do you burst in here?

1447
01:53:24,221 --> 01:53:26,056
找到达布堤了
We have found Tuptim.

1448
01:53:29,059 --> 01:53:32,145
她在哪？
现在还在调查中
- Where is she?
- Secret police are questioning her.

1449
01:53:32,229 --> 01:53:34,439
但那个男的还没抓到
Her lover has not been caught.
Not yet.

1450
01:53:34,773 --> 01:53:35,899
她的什么？
What?

1451
01:53:35,983 --> 01:53:38,694
那个要和达布堤一起私奔的就是伦塔
It is believed she was
running away with Lun Tha...

1452
01:53:38,777 --> 01:53:40,779
送她来这儿的缅甸使者
...man who bring her here
from Burma.

1453
01:53:42,072 --> 01:53:43,365
这是何等的耻辱
Dishonor.

1454
01:53:44,491 --> 01:53:46,243
这是何等的耻辱
Dishonor. Dishonor!

1455
01:53:47,327 --> 01:53:50,497
把她带上来
但是，陛下，你想对她怎么样？
- Bring her in.
- Your Majesty, what will you do?

1456
01:53:50,581 --> 01:53:52,875
我会让她知道厉害的
I shall do what is usually done
in such event.

1457
01:53:53,250 --> 01:53:54,751
不，不
No. No!

1458
01:53:55,335 --> 01:53:58,839
不要，安娜夫人，让他们不要罚我！
No! Mrs. Anna,
do not let them beat me.

1459
01:53:58,922 --> 01:54:00,716
让他们不要！
Do not let them!

1460
01:54:01,508 --> 01:54:04,011
男的在那？
我不知道
- Where is this man?
- I do not know.

1461
01:54:04,094 --> 01:54:06,054
你早就和那个男的相好了
It is known you were lovers with him.

1462
01:54:06,138 --> 01:54:08,307
我是冤枉的！
I was not lovers with this man!

1463
01:54:08,390 --> 01:54:09,641
不知羞耻的贱人
Dishonor!

1464
01:54:11,101 --> 01:54:14,938
会让你招供的！
住手！听见了没有？
- We will have truth of you.
- Stop that! Do you hear? Stop it!

1465
01:54:15,647 --> 01:54:17,983
你能明白就再好不过了
It is better
if you understand at once...

1466
01:54:18,066 --> 01:54:20,068
这件事与你无关
...that this does not concern you.

1467
01:54:20,152 --> 01:54:23,322
我是为陛下着想,所以不能袖手旁观…
Oh, but it does, Your Majesty.
It does, dreadfully.

1468
01:54:23,405 --> 01:54:26,200
为她，更是为您
Because of her,
and even more because of you.

1469
01:54:26,283 --> 01:54:29,161
她只是个孩子,我想她是因为不快乐才逃走的
She's a child, running away
because she was unhappy.

1470
01:54:29,244 --> 01:54:30,787
陛下，你放过她吧？
Can't you understand that?

1471
01:54:30,871 --> 01:54:32,372
你是在浪费时间！
You waste my time!

1472
01:54:32,456 --> 01:54:35,626
陛下，请您想想即使你惩罚她又能怎么样呢
I beg of you not to take revenge
on this girl.

1473
01:54:35,709 --> 01:54:40,172
那只会将你一直以来的努力全部化为乌有
You'll throw away everything you've
accomplished for yourself and country.

1474
01:54:40,255 --> 01:54:43,967
而你只是因为虚荣心受伤,她并没有伤着你的心
The girl hurt your vanity, that's all.
She didn't hurt your heart.

1475
01:54:44,051 --> 01:54:45,594
你没有爱心！
You have no heart!

1476
01:54:45,677 --> 01:54:48,472
也从来没有爱过任何人！
You've never loved anyone
and you never will.

1477
01:54:48,555 --> 01:54:50,098
把鞭子给我！给我！
I will show you. Give me.

1478
01:54:50,182 --> 01:54:53,018
我真不敢相信你真的想打她吗
I can't believe you will do
this dreadful thing!

1479
01:54:53,101 --> 01:54:57,105
不相信，是吗？等你听到哀嚎之后就会夺门而出了！
You don't? Believe when you hear
her screams as you run from here.

1480
01:54:57,189 --> 01:55:00,859
我不会逃走的，要待在这看到最后
I am not going to run. I am going
to stand here and watch you.

1481
01:55:01,318 --> 01:55:03,320
这个女人由我亲自来处罚
Hold this girl. I do this myself!

1482
01:55:03,403 --> 01:55:05,155
你是个野蛮人
You are a barbarian.

1483
01:55:06,615 --> 01:55:07,616
趴下，趴下
Down, down, down!

1484
01:55:09,660 --> 01:55:11,787
当我是国王了吗？
Am I king or am I not king?

1485
01:55:12,246 --> 01:55:17,334
在我的王宫里不允许有这种事发生
我没有义务听一个教师的指示
Am I to be cuckold in my own palace,
to take orders from English teacher?

1486
01:55:17,417 --> 01:55:19,169
不，陛下，这不是指示
闭嘴！
- No, no. Not orders.
- Silence!

1487
01:55:19,586 --> 01:55:21,922
我打从娘胎里下来就是国王了
I am king as I was born to be...

1488
01:55:22,840 --> 01:55:25,509
我要以自己的方式来治理我的王国--
...and Siam to be governed
in my way!

1489
01:55:25,592 --> 01:55:27,928
而不是英国或者法国或者是中国的那些方式！
Not English way, not French way,
not Chinese way!

1490
01:55:28,428 --> 01:55:29,638
以我自己的方式！
My Way!

1491
01:55:30,514 --> 01:55:32,266
你说我是个野蛮人
Barbarian, you say.

1492
01:55:33,016 --> 01:55:36,144
那总要比那个软弱的国王要好得多
There is no barbarian worse
than a weak king.

1493
01:55:36,228 --> 01:55:38,230
现在我让你见识一下我的强壮？
And I am strong, do you hear?

1494
01:55:38,313 --> 01:55:39,523
我的强壮
Strong!

1495
01:56:02,504 --> 01:56:03,589
怎么回事？
Well?

1496
01:56:03,672 --> 01:56:07,551
男人的尸体在河中被发现了
The man, the lover has been found
in river. He is dead.

1497
01:56:07,885 --> 01:56:09,011
他死了
Dead?

1498
01:56:09,720 --> 01:56:11,096
噢，不
Oh, no!

1499
01:56:12,181 --> 01:56:13,390
噢，不
Oh, no!

1500
01:56:14,057 --> 01:56:16,018
噢，不
Oh, no!

1501
01:56:18,812 --> 01:56:22,524
我真的无法理解
你们还有国王
I don't understand you,
not you or your king.

1502
01:56:22,608 --> 01:56:24,568
我不理解你们
I'll never understand him.

1503
01:56:24,651 --> 01:56:25,944
你！
YOU!

1504
01:56:26,570 --> 01:56:29,656
我怕发生这种事故,早就警告过你
When I warn you of this
many months ago, you do not listen.

1505
01:56:30,449 --> 01:56:32,367
你毁了他
You have destroyed him.

1506
01:56:32,784 --> 01:56:34,786
陛下已不是从前的陛下了
He can never be the king
he was before.

1507
01:56:34,870 --> 01:56:37,164
都是你把国王变得软弱了
You have taken all that
away from him.

1508
01:56:37,247 --> 01:56:39,124
都是因为你
You have destroyed king!

1509
01:56:39,208 --> 01:56:42,753
不管上哪都行,我要搭下班船走
The next boat that comes, no matter
where it goes, I shall be on it.

1510
01:56:45,631 --> 01:56:47,883
我要走，请把这个还给国王
Give this back to His Majesty.

1511
01:56:48,425 --> 01:56:51,094
你不应该到这儿来
I wish you have never come to Siam.

1512
01:56:51,470 --> 01:56:52,846
是的
So do I.

1513
01:56:52,930 --> 01:56:54,932
我不应该到这儿来
Oh, so do I!

1514
01:57:48,318 --> 01:57:49,486
妈妈
Mother.

1515
01:57:51,405 --> 01:57:53,615
妈妈，我们的行李已经准备好了
Mother, our luggage is all loaded.

1516
01:57:53,699 --> 01:57:55,826
船也快要开了
We'll be late for the boat.

1517
01:57:56,451 --> 01:57:57,828
好的，路易
Yes, Louis.

1518
01:57:58,328 --> 01:57:59,663
我立刻就去
I'm coming.

1519
01:58:03,792 --> 01:58:05,419
安娜夫人
Mrs. Anna.

1520
01:58:05,586 --> 01:58:08,130
张妃，谢谢你
Lady Thiang. Your Highness.

1521
01:58:08,213 --> 01:58:10,924
来为我送行
How nice of you
to come to say goodbye.

1522
01:58:11,008 --> 01:58:13,760
不，我不是来送行的
Mrs. Anna, I do not come for myself.

1523
01:58:13,844 --> 01:58:16,221
我是希望你立刻去见陛下
I come for one
who must see you quickly.

1524
01:58:17,264 --> 01:58:20,434
你应该告诉他我现在已经不是他的仆女
You may tell His Majesty
I am no longer subject to him.

1525
01:58:20,517 --> 01:58:22,436
你什么也不知道
You do not understand.

1526
01:58:23,187 --> 01:58:24,605
安娜夫人…
Mrs. Anna...

1527
01:58:25,147 --> 01:58:26,690
他快死了
...he is dying!

1528
01:58:28,358 --> 01:58:29,776
快死了？
Dying?

1529
01:58:29,860 --> 01:58:31,111
陛下？
The king?

1530
01:58:32,196 --> 01:58:35,157
不，张妃，出什么事了？
Oh, no, Lady Thiang.
What happened?

1531
01:58:36,533 --> 01:58:39,703
没人知道是怎么回事？
Who can say what it is
that makes a man die?

1532
01:58:41,079 --> 01:58:44,833
他一定是过度忧伤而招致死亡的
A sad heart that no longer wishes
to go on beating?

1533
01:58:46,126 --> 01:58:50,297
那天晚宴后，他就避开人
Ever since night of great banquet,
he has shut himself away in palace...

1534
01:58:50,380 --> 01:58:52,549
封闭在自己的世界里
...turning from all
who would speak to him...

1535
01:58:52,925 --> 01:58:56,011
不吃不睡，废寝忘食的看着书…
...unwilling to sleep
or to nourish himself...

1536
01:58:56,762 --> 01:59:00,766
并时时地叹息着
...searching through many books,
only to push them aside in despair.

1537
01:59:02,059 --> 01:59:05,354
御医劝了他很多次…
Doctors warned him he must
change his ways quickly...

1538
01:59:06,563 --> 01:59:09,066
但他都不听，安娜夫人
...but he would not listen, Mrs. Anna.

1539
01:59:10,192 --> 01:59:11,944
他完全不听别人的劝告
He would not listen.

1540
01:59:12,903 --> 01:59:14,404
我怎么什么都不知道呢
I had no idea.

1541
01:59:15,614 --> 01:59:18,534
因为他禁止将这件事张扬出去…
Everyone who knew
was forbidden to speak of it.

1542
01:59:19,868 --> 01:59:22,371
御医说这是迟早的问题
And now,
doctors have no hope for him.

1543
01:59:24,331 --> 01:59:25,541
安娜夫人
Mrs. Anna.

1544
01:59:26,333 --> 01:59:27,709
殿下
Your Highness.

1545
01:59:27,793 --> 01:59:29,503
我很害怕，安娜夫人
I am frightened, Mrs. Anna.

1546
01:59:29,878 --> 01:59:32,589
因为我很爱父王…
I am frightened
because I love my father...

1547
01:59:32,673 --> 01:59:36,385
如果他死了我就得继承王位
...and also because if he dies,
I shall be king.

1548
01:59:37,219 --> 01:59:39,346
我应该怎么样去当国王？
And I do not know how to be.

1549
01:59:42,140 --> 01:59:45,936
孩子，等你当国王后再学习也不晚，真的
Many men learn this after
they become kings, Your Highness.

1550
01:59:47,104 --> 01:59:49,314
你只要把老师教过你的事再回想一下
It will be good to think back...

1551
01:59:49,398 --> 01:59:52,025
国王交给我这封信
...on all that
Mrs. Anna has taught you.

1552
01:59:55,362 --> 01:59:59,116
希望在你离开前交给你
When king heard you were sailing
tonight, he started to write letter.

1553
01:59:59,867 --> 02:00:02,411
他非常困难地
完成了这封信…
It was difficult for him, Mrs. Anna.

1554
02:00:03,245 --> 02:00:04,788
非常困难
Very difficult.

1555
02:00:05,581 --> 02:00:08,208
他要我转交给你
He has commanded
that I give it to you.

1556
02:00:16,925 --> 02:00:20,762
安娜夫人，你能把信念给我们听听吗？
Please, may I hear what
my father has said, Mrs. Anna?

1557
02:00:34,318 --> 02:00:36,320
"你好，安娜
"While I am lying here...

1558
02:00:36,695 --> 02:00:38,697
"看来我活不久了
...I think perhaps I die.

1559
02:00:39,781 --> 02:00:42,367
"虽然我从没想到
This heart which you say
I have not got...

1560
02:00:42,492 --> 02:00:44,286
"这会发生得这么快
...is matter of concern.

1561
02:00:45,954 --> 02:00:50,167
"对我来说死应该是很平常的事
"It occurs to me that there shall be
nothing wrong that men shall die.

1562
02:00:51,001 --> 02:00:53,086
"我也没有什么好遗憾的
"For all that matters about man...

1563
02:00:53,170 --> 02:00:56,298
"问题在于我是否做到了最好
...is that he shall have tried
his utmost best.

1564
02:00:57,841 --> 02:01:02,095
"想想你也为本国
In looking back, I discover that
you think much on those people

1565
02:01:02,596 --> 02:01:05,432
尽了最大的努力
...who require that you live up
to best of self.

1566
02:01:07,184 --> 02:01:09,853
"因为你经常会说出实话
You have spoken truth
to me always...

1567
02:01:10,896 --> 02:01:14,066
"所以有时我会感到很气愤
...and for this I have often
lost my temper on you.

1568
02:01:15,567 --> 02:01:17,611
"但是安娜,在我死之前
But now I do not wish to die...

1569
02:01:17,694 --> 02:01:20,531
"我诚心向你表示感谢
...without saying this gratitude...

1570
02:01:21,865 --> 02:01:25,202
以及等等的
...and large respect,
et cetera, et cetera.

1571
02:01:26,954 --> 02:01:28,622
"安娜，你以女子之躯…
"I think it very strange...

1572
02:01:28,705 --> 02:01:32,000
"竟然那么能干…
...that a woman shall have been
most earnest help of all.

1573
02:01:33,710 --> 02:01:35,629
"可是，安娜，你要知道…
But, Mrs. Anna,
you must remember...

1574
02:01:35,712 --> 02:01:38,715
"你真的是个很顽固的女人…
...that you have been
a very difficult woman...

1575
02:01:40,050 --> 02:01:43,053
"我认为没有别的女人会向你一样，与众不同
...and much more difficult
than generality."

1576
02:01:48,100 --> 02:01:50,018
我们得回去了
We must hurry back now.

1577
02:01:51,854 --> 02:01:53,355
你会来吗？
You will come?

1578
02:02:18,338 --> 02:02:19,590
妈妈
Mother...

1579
02:02:19,840 --> 02:02:22,092
现在国王快死了
...now that the king is dying...

1580
02:02:22,176 --> 02:02:24,261
你们会和好吗？
...does that make you friends again?

1581
02:02:25,137 --> 02:02:26,930
是的，路易斯
I suppose so, Louis.

1582
02:02:27,639 --> 02:02:30,058
我们不能再彼此伤害了
We can't hurt each other anymore.

1583
02:02:31,351 --> 02:02:33,312
他是个可怕的人
He always frightened me.

1584
02:02:34,771 --> 02:02:36,523
如果你了解他的话
I wish you had known him better.

1585
02:02:36,607 --> 02:02:39,067
一定会和他成为朋友的
You two could have been
such good friends.

1586
02:02:40,277 --> 02:02:43,113
他有些地方很孩子气
In many ways he was
just as young as you.

1587
02:02:45,365 --> 02:02:47,910
你认为他是个好国王吗？
Was he as good a king
as he could have been?

1588
02:02:50,329 --> 02:02:54,416
是的，我认为再也没有比他更好的国王了
I don't think any man has ever been
as good a king as he could have been.

1589
02:02:55,918 --> 02:02:57,628
他都尝试过了
But this one tried.

1590
02:02:58,545 --> 02:03:00,297
而且非常的努力
He tried very hard.

1591
02:03:03,592 --> 02:03:06,053
你喜欢国王是吗，妈妈？
You really like him,
don't you, Mother?

1592
02:03:06,803 --> 02:03:08,138
是的，路易
Yes, Louis.

1593
02:03:09,139 --> 02:03:10,933
我非常喜欢他…
I like him very much.

1594
02:03:12,100 --> 02:03:13,727
非常喜欢
Very much indeed.

1595
02:03:46,510 --> 02:03:47,970
几个星期没见你了…
Several weeks...

1596
02:03:48,512 --> 02:03:50,138
安娜夫人
...I do not see you, Mrs. Anna.

1597
02:03:51,682 --> 02:03:53,183
我快死了
And now I die.

1598
02:03:54,017 --> 02:03:55,853
不会的，陛下
Oh, no, Your Majesty.

1599
02:03:56,270 --> 02:03:58,188
这是很不科学的回答
This is not scientific.

1600
02:03:59,982 --> 02:04:01,233
我知道…
I know...

1601
02:04:01,775 --> 02:04:03,694
自己什么时候死
...if I die or do not die.

1602
02:04:04,862 --> 02:04:07,698
你不该来的，你不回自己的寝室吗？
You shouldn't be here.
Can't we move you to your room?

1603
02:04:08,115 --> 02:04:09,157
不
No.

1604
02:04:09,867 --> 02:04:12,494
这个房间比较好，这里是知识的宝库
I wish to remain here
in room with knowledge.

1605
02:04:16,540 --> 02:04:18,333
你要回国了？
You are leaving Siam?

1606
02:04:19,293 --> 02:04:20,377
什么时候走
When?

1607
02:04:20,711 --> 02:04:22,504
很快就走，陛下
Very soon, Your Majesty.

1608
02:04:22,588 --> 02:04:25,048
我只能在这儿逗留一会儿，
陛下
In fact, I can stay
only a few more minutes.

1609
02:04:25,340 --> 02:04:27,342
你很高兴吗？
And you are glad of this?

1610
02:04:28,468 --> 02:04:30,095
泰国的人民…
People of Siam...

1611
02:04:30,804 --> 02:04:33,098
王子，公主们
...royal children, et cetera...

1612
02:04:33,891 --> 02:04:35,100
他们并不高兴
...are not glad.

1613
02:04:35,851 --> 02:04:38,770
大家因为你要回国…
And all are in great affliction...

1614
02:04:40,189 --> 02:04:41,565
而感到很悲伤，很难过
...of your departure.

1615
02:04:43,317 --> 02:04:44,985
我会相信他们的
I shall miss them.

1616
02:04:45,068 --> 02:04:46,904
你会相信他们的
You shall miss them...

1617
02:04:47,571 --> 02:04:49,072
但是你要走了
...but you shall be leaving.

1618
02:04:52,326 --> 02:04:53,535
我，也是
I, too...

1619
02:04:53,952 --> 02:04:55,329
要走了
...am leaving.

1620
02:04:55,913 --> 02:04:57,748
只是不用乘船…
Only I'm not walking onto a boat...

1621
02:04:57,831 --> 02:04:59,708
甚至不是我自己的意志
...with my own feet...

1622
02:05:00,083 --> 02:05:02,211
我要走了
...of my own free will.

1623
02:05:05,547 --> 02:05:07,216
是该走了
I am just leaving.

1624
02:05:10,052 --> 02:05:11,970
你的头为什么要比我高？
Why is your head higher than mine?

1625
02:05:21,063 --> 02:05:22,147
这个
Here.

1626
02:05:24,775 --> 02:05:27,611
是你的
Here is something belonging to you.

1627
02:05:27,694 --> 02:05:29,029
戴上
Put it on.

1628
02:05:29,488 --> 02:05:31,281
把它戴上！
戴上！
Put it on, put it on.

1629
02:05:34,117 --> 02:05:35,369
请你
Please...

1630
02:05:35,452 --> 02:05:36,578
戴上它
...wear it.

1631
02:05:49,466 --> 02:05:50,968
孩子们来了
The children.

1632
02:05:53,178 --> 02:05:54,388
孩子们靠近我
Let my children come in.

1633
02:06:05,399 --> 02:06:07,276
晚安，孩子们
Good evening, children.

1634
02:06:07,359 --> 02:06:09,611
晚安，父皇
Good evening, my father.

1635
02:06:09,695 --> 02:06:13,156
老师，请你别走！
- Please, do not go. We'll miss you!
- Children!

1636
02:06:13,240 --> 02:06:14,825
孩子们，不可以
Stop this noise.

1637
02:06:15,284 --> 02:06:17,953
你们是来探望父王还是安娜夫人
Did you come to see your father
or Mrs. Anna?

1638
02:06:18,328 --> 02:06:20,289
没关系的，张妃
It is all right, Lady Thiang.

1639
02:06:20,372 --> 02:06:21,915
难怪他们会这样
It is suitable.

1640
02:06:22,666 --> 02:06:24,001
父王
My father.

1641
02:06:25,961 --> 02:06:27,838
什么事，雅欧拉克
Princess Ying Yaowalak.

1642
02:06:28,589 --> 02:06:31,008
我想请求你…
I have wish to--

1643
02:06:32,843 --> 02:06:35,762
她是想传话给安娜夫人
She has memorized message
for Mrs. Anna.

1644
02:06:37,222 --> 02:06:38,765
你说吧
Speak message now.

1645
02:06:42,144 --> 02:06:43,645
说吧
Say it, say it, say it.

1646
02:06:43,729 --> 02:06:46,648
我们的良师良友
Dear friend and teacher...

1647
02:06:46,732 --> 02:06:49,568
拜托你
...my goodness gracious...

1648
02:06:49,651 --> 02:06:52,279
别离去
...do not go away.

1649
02:06:52,362 --> 02:06:54,907
因为我们都需要你
We are in great need of you.

1650
02:06:55,532 --> 02:06:57,367
我们就像眼睛看不见的盲人
We are like one blind.

1651
02:06:58,076 --> 02:07:01,371
求你别弃我们于黑暗不顾
Do not let us fall down in darkness.

1652
02:07:01,872 --> 02:07:05,459
再象以前般温柔的…
Continue good and sincere...

1653
02:07:05,542 --> 02:07:08,337
守护并指引
...concern for us...

1654
02:07:08,420 --> 02:07:10,631
我们上正道
...and lead us in right road.

1655
02:07:11,006 --> 02:07:12,758
你的学生
Your loving pupil...

1656
02:07:12,841 --> 02:07:15,552
雅欧拉克公主
...Princess Ying Yaowalak.

1657
02:07:28,398 --> 02:07:29,566
妈妈
Mother...

1658
02:07:29,650 --> 02:07:32,194
船要开了我们走吧
...it's the boat. It's time to go.

1659
02:07:32,277 --> 02:07:35,030
请不要走，安娜夫人
- Do not go, Mrs. Anna.
- Please do not go.

1660
02:07:35,113 --> 02:07:36,907
安娜夫人，你别走
No, no, Mrs. Anna!

1661
02:07:57,469 --> 02:08:01,181
路易，马上告诉船长把行李卸下，快点拿回来
Run down to the boat and ask
Captain Orton to take our things off.

1662
02:08:01,974 --> 02:08:03,350
是的，妈妈
Yes, Mother.

1663
02:08:09,898 --> 02:08:11,108
安静
Silence!

1664
02:08:13,443 --> 02:08:16,405
这没什么好兴奋的
There's no reason
for doing of demonstration...

1665
02:08:17,197 --> 02:08:20,284
她只是尽了老师的职责而矣
...for schoolteacher
realizing her duty...

1666
02:08:21,368 --> 02:08:24,162
而且我还付给她高薪呢…
...for which I pay her
exorbitant monthly fee...

1667
02:08:25,163 --> 02:08:26,415
一个月…
...of...

1668
02:08:28,125 --> 02:08:31,378
25英磅
...twenty-five pounds.

1669
02:08:33,422 --> 02:08:34,798
还有…
Furthermore...

1670
02:08:36,884 --> 02:08:40,637
在临死国王的枕边…
...this is disorganized behavior...

1671
02:08:41,889 --> 02:08:44,016
如此的吵闹，实在是不敬
...in presence of dying king.

1672
02:08:47,311 --> 02:08:48,812
皇太子…
Chulalongkorn.

1673
02:08:49,980 --> 02:08:51,106
站起来
Rise.

1674
02:08:53,317 --> 02:08:54,651
安娜夫人
Mrs. Anna...

1675
02:08:56,904 --> 02:08:58,405
你
...you...

1676
02:08:58,488 --> 02:08:59,990
来当书记
...take notes.

1677
02:09:03,160 --> 02:09:04,828
记下我的笔录…
You take notes...

1678
02:09:07,164 --> 02:09:09,333
说给下一任国王
...from next king.

1679
02:09:16,006 --> 02:09:17,090
好吧
Well?

1680
02:09:17,674 --> 02:09:19,468
如果你当了国王
Suppose you are king.

1681
02:09:20,302 --> 02:09:22,471
会怎么样呢？
Is there nothing you would do?

1682
02:09:22,554 --> 02:09:24,097
我
I...

1683
02:09:24,181 --> 02:09:26,308
我会下令
...would make proclamations.

1684
02:09:26,683 --> 02:09:28,352
是的。什么令呢？
Yes. Yes?

1685
02:09:29,186 --> 02:09:32,272
首先，我会在过年时
First, I would proclaim
for coming New Year...

1686
02:09:32,648 --> 02:09:34,107
放烟火
...fireworks.

1687
02:09:34,191 --> 02:09:36,109
哈哈
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

1688
02:09:36,193 --> 02:09:37,819
还要举办划舟竞赛
Also boat races.

1689
02:09:38,529 --> 02:09:39,863
划舟竞赛？
Boat races?

1690
02:09:40,364 --> 02:09:43,033
为什么要在新年举办划舟竞赛呢？
Why boat races
with New Year's celebration?

1691
02:09:44,701 --> 02:09:46,370
我喜欢划舟竞赛呢
I like boat races.

1692
02:09:46,912 --> 02:09:49,706
然后我会下第二道命令
And, Father, I would make
second proclamation.

1693
02:09:49,873 --> 02:09:52,167
好的，什么是第二道命令？
说说看
Yes, what is second proclamation?
Make it, make it.

1694
02:09:52,960 --> 02:09:55,504
这种象青蛙似的向国王行礼…
Regarding custom
of bowing to king...

1695
02:09:56,213 --> 02:09:58,215
要废除掉
...in fashion of lowly toad.

1696
02:09:59,967 --> 02:10:02,010
我认为
I do not believe this is good thing.

1697
02:10:02,094 --> 02:10:04,471
勉强别人不是一件好事
Causing embarrassing fatigue
of body...

1698
02:10:04,555 --> 02:10:06,974
会让国民的心卑微
...degrading experience for soul...

1699
02:10:07,057 --> 02:10:09,142
等等，等等
...et cetera, et cetera, et cetera.

1700
02:10:09,226 --> 02:10:10,894
很不好…
This is bad thing.

1701
02:10:12,437 --> 02:10:14,606
我觉得应该废除掉
I believe.

1702
02:10:20,445 --> 02:10:23,073
你会对我生气吗，父王？
You are angry with me, my father?

1703
02:10:23,740 --> 02:10:26,618
为什么要问这种事呢？
Oh, why do you ask question?

1704
02:10:27,744 --> 02:10:29,413
只要继续位了
If you are king...

1705
02:10:30,539 --> 02:10:32,791
你就是国王！
...you are king!

1706
02:10:34,751 --> 02:10:37,045
别问一个生病的人…
Don't ask question of sick man.

1707
02:10:39,381 --> 02:10:40,424
还有
Nor...

1708
02:10:41,216 --> 02:10:42,467
女人的意见
...of woman.

1709
02:10:44,178 --> 02:10:45,929
也想废除…
This proclamation...

1710
02:10:46,972 --> 02:10:48,932
对国王伏地下跪的事…
...against bowing to king...

1711
02:10:50,100 --> 02:10:53,729
要由你来负责
...I believe to be your fault.

1712
02:10:55,480 --> 02:10:57,608
要真能那样做就好了
Oh, I hope so, Your Majesty.

1713
02:10:58,942 --> 02:11:00,444
我早就盼望着有这一天了
I do hope so.

1714
02:11:02,821 --> 02:11:04,448
大家站起来
Up! Rise up!

1715
02:11:09,536 --> 02:11:10,746
父王？
Father?

1716
02:11:12,497 --> 02:11:13,874
起来，起来
Up,up,up!

1717
02:11:15,167 --> 02:11:17,419
像士兵一样排成一队
Like soldiers in lines.

1718
02:11:21,340 --> 02:11:22,966
就像他刚才说的一样…
It has been said.

1719
02:11:24,593 --> 02:11:26,929
今后表示敬意时…
There shall be no more bowing...

1720
02:11:28,805 --> 02:11:30,432
不用这样
...for showing...

1721
02:11:30,974 --> 02:11:32,434
对国王
...respect...

1722
02:11:33,310 --> 02:11:34,728
行礼
...for king.

1723
02:11:39,983 --> 02:11:42,027
那是治理国家的王者…
It has been said by one...

1724
02:11:44,947 --> 02:11:46,907
富有经验的智者…
...who has been trained...

1725
02:11:48,283 --> 02:11:50,035
所说的
...for royal...

1726
02:11:51,078 --> 02:11:52,579
至理明言
...government.

1727
02:12:05,759 --> 02:12:08,178
今后不必象青蛙一样行礼
There shall be no bowing like toad.

1728
02:12:08,262 --> 02:12:09,513
不再蹲伏
No crouching.

1729
02:12:09,596 --> 02:12:11,348
不再爬行
No crawling.

1730
02:12:11,431 --> 02:12:15,561
但并不是要你们不尊敬国王
This does not mean, however,
that you do not show respect for king.

1731
02:12:16,186 --> 02:12:18,814
你们要像这样挺起胸膛…
You will stand with shoulders back...

1732
02:12:18,897 --> 02:12:21,024
抬起头。就像这样
...and chin high, like this.

1733
02:12:22,359 --> 02:12:25,070
像国王一样气宇轩昂
You will face king
with proud expression...

1734
02:12:25,153 --> 02:12:28,240
像国王一样高傲
...showing pride in self
as well as in king.

1735
02:12:29,575 --> 02:12:33,161
相互尊重才是正确的礼仪
This is proper way for men
to show esteem for one another...

1736
02:12:33,412 --> 02:12:37,541
眼睛和眼睛相对才有人性的尊严
...by looking upon each other's faces
with calmness of spirit...

1737
02:12:37,833 --> 02:12:40,669
平等的凝望
...eyes meeting eyes in equal gaze...

1738
02:12:40,752 --> 02:12:44,548
像个男人般挺胸站立
...bodies upright, standing as men
were meant to stand...

1739
02:12:44,923 --> 02:12:47,593
平等尊重
...with dignity and awareness of self.

1740
02:12:48,302 --> 02:12:50,387
从现在开始
So from this day forward...

1741
